Controls the max interest group lifetime in milliseconds. If
kFledgeMaxGroupLifetimeFeature is enabled, then the max interest group
lifetime will be kFledgeMaxGroupLifetimeFeature; otherwise, it will be 30
days.

*WARNING*: Some UMA histograms assume a particular max lifetime for the
purposes of choosing appropriate bucketing, such as
Ads.InterestGroup.Auction.GroupFreshness*. As bucketing should not be changed
for an existing metric, consider adding a new metric with new bucketing if
increasing this value.

NOTE: This value is only enforced when interest groups are joined -- the
lifetimes of groups already in the database will not be affected.

Name: kWebAuthnAmbientSignin
Documentation: Enable non-autofill sign-in UI for conditional mediation.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromUnknown
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, requests to localhost initiated from non-secure
contexts in the `unknown` IP address space are blocked.

See also:
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests

Name: kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity
Documentation:
Configures FLEDGE to consider k-anonymity. If both
kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity and kFledgeEnforceKAnonymity are on it will be
enforced; if only kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity is on it will be simulated.

Turning on kFledgeEnforceKAnonymity alone does nothing.

Name: kWebAssemblyDeopt
Documentation:
Enable WebAssembly deoptimization support (not user visible), see
https://crbug.com/42204618.

Name: kFledgeEnableUserAgentOverrides
Documentation: Enable the user agent header in auction requests to be overridden.

Name: kTimeLimitedInsecureCookies
Documentation:
Enables expiration duration limit (3 hours) for cookies on insecure websites.
This feature is a no-op unless kEnableSchemeBoundCookies is enabled.

Name: kEnableAsyncNotificationManagerForDownload
Documentation: Whether to enable async notification manager for downloads.

Name: kFullscreenSignInPromoUseDate
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/408962000): This feature is going to be used after clients
have the required information in local storage.

Name: kHstsTopLevelNavigationsOnly
Documentation: When enabled HSTS upgrades will only apply to top-level navigations.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, private network requests initiated from
non-secure contexts in the `public` address space  are blocked.

See also:
 - https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#integration-fetch
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromPrivate
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromUnknown

Name: kAnimateSuggestionsListAppearance
Documentation: Animate appearance of suggestions list.

Name: kPermissionSiteSettingsRadioButton
Documentation:
When enabled, site settings pages use radio button groups other than toggles.
In the meanwhile, CPSS if exist will be a separate radio button group.

Name: kDesktopPWAsTabStripSettings
Documentation: Adds a user settings that allows PWAs to be opened with a tab strip.

Name: kFedCmDelegation
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM Delegation API.

Name: kAutofillOverridePredictions
Documentation:
Allows passing a set of overrides for Autofill server predictions.
Example command line to override server predictions manually:
chrome --enable-features=AutofillOverridePredictions:spec/1_2_4-7_8_9
This creates two manual overrides that supersede server predictions as
follows:
* The server prediction for the field with signature 2 in the form with
  signature 1 is overridden to be 4 (NAME_MIDDLE).
* The server prediction for the field with signature 8 in the form with
  signature 7 is overridden to be 9 (EMAIL_ADDRESS).

See
components/autofill/core/browser/crowdsourcing/server_prediction_overrides.h
for more examples and details on how to specify overrides.

Name: kVideoDecodeBatching
Documentation:
Controls whether to pre-dispatch more decode tasks when pending decodes is
smaller than maximum supported decodes as advertiszed by decoder.

Name: kLoadingPredictorDisregardAlwaysAccessesNetwork
Documentation:
Modifies loading predictor so that the value of the |always_access_network|
attribute is not used when computing the predicting score for an origin.

Name: kEnableMSAAOnNewIntelGPUs
Documentation: Enables the use of MSAA in skia on Ice Lake and later intel architectures.

Name: kDirectCompositorThreadIpc
Documentation:
Enables input IPC to directly target the renderer's compositor thread without
hopping through the IO thread first.

Name: kMigrateAlwaysTranslateLanguagesFix
Documentation:
Whether to migrate the obsolete always-translate languages pref to the new
pref during object construction as a fix for crbug/1291356, which had
previously not been migrated at all on iOS. This also enables a more
conservative pref merging process that aims to merge in old always-translate
language values from the obsolete pref without conflicting with any values in
the new pref that may have been added.

TODO(crbug.com/40826252): This base::Feature only exists to allow a less
risky merge into iOS M98. This base::Feature should be removed once it's no
longer relevant and the enabled behavior should become the only behavior.

Name: kBackgroundTracingPerformanceMark
Documentation:
Used to configure a per-origin allowlist of performance.mark events that are
permitted to be included in slow reports traces. See crbug.com/1181774.

Name: kModelExecutionCapabilityDisable
Documentation: Feature for disabling the model execution user account capability check.

Name: kDecoupleSafeSitesFromMainSwitch
Documentation:
Allows reading SafeSites setting without extra supervised user guard. Can be
enabled iff kAlignSafeSitesValueWithBrowserDefault is also enabled.

Name: kFrequencyCappingForLargeStickyAdDetection
Documentation:
Enables the frequency capping for detecting large sticky ads.
Large-sticky-ads are those ads that stick to the bottom of the page
regardless of a user’s efforts to scroll, and take up more than 30% of the
screen’s real estate.

Name: kFledge
Documentation: FLEDGE ad serving runtime flag/JS API.

Name: kFledgeLimitSelectableBuyerAndSellerReportingIdsFetchedFromKAnon
Documentation:
Feature flag to limit on the number of
`selectableBuyerAndSellerReportingIds` for which the browser fetches k-anon
keys.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformAdaptiveToolbarV2Feature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling adaptive toolbar v2 multi-output model.

Name: kPasswordFormClientsideClassifier
Documentation: Enables running the clientside form classifier to parse password forms.

Name: kDisableShortcutsEnableDiy
Documentation:
A feature to disable shortcut creation from the Chrome UI, and instead use
that to create DIY apps.

Name: kIdentifiabilityStudy
Documentation:
Root feature for all identifiability study logic.

If the feature is disabled, then this browser instance will not be
participating in the identifiability study. I.e. no identifiability metrics
will be recorded or reported.

Enabling the feature doesn't automatically make this client part of the study
either.

Name: kEnterpriseUrlFilteringEventReportingOnAndroid
Documentation:
Controls whether url filtering event reporting is enabled on Android, even if
`kEnterpriseSecurityEventReportingOnAndroid` is not enabled.

Name: kPrivacySandboxInternalsDevUI
Documentation: Enables chrome://privacy-sandbox-internals DevUI page.

Name: kUseNewAlpsCodepointQUIC
Documentation:
Enables using the new ALPS codepoint to negotiate application settings for
QUIC.

Name: kSiteIsolationForOAuthSites
Documentation:
Controls a mode for dynamically process-isolating sites where the user has
logged in via OAuth.  These sites are determined by runtime heuristics.

This is intended to be used primarily when full site isolation is turned
off.  To check whether this mode is enabled, use
SiteIsolationPolicy::IsIsolationForOAuthSitesEnabled() rather than
checking the feature directly, since that decision is influenced by other
factors as well.

This feature does not affect Android Webview, which does not include this
code.

Name: kMediaSessionService
Documentation:
Enables the Media Session service including audio focus tracking. This allows
clients to consume the Media Session Mojo APIs but should not have any
changes to behavior. It is enabled by default on all platforms except Android.

Name: kAutofillLogUKMEventsWithSamplingOnSession
Documentation:
Enable the feature by default, and set the enabled percentage as a feature
param. We are logging information of field types, autofill status and
forms with a defined sampling rate of 10% on sessions.
Autofill FormSummary/FieldInfo UKM schema:
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ZH0JbL6bES3cD4KqZWsGR6n8I-rhnkx6no6nQOgYq5w/.

Name: kUseStructuralSignatureInsteadOfSecondary
Documentation:
Replaces the secondary signature with the structural signature for Uploads.
For Queries still only the secondary (alternative) signature is used.
TODO(crbug.com/431737839): Clean up when roll out finishes successfully.

Name: kLensOverlayTranslateLanguages
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay translate button.

Name: kOriginIsolationMemoryThreshold
Documentation:
Desktop-only: kOriginIsolationMemoryThreshold (if enabled) is used to
determine if a device has the necessary resources to participate in origin
isolation (a stronger model than site isolation, but with potentially higher
resource usage).

Name: kPlusAddressFallbackFromContextMenu
Documentation: When enabled, plus addresses are supported within the context menu.

Name: kLensOverlayBackToPage
Documentation: Enables the back to live page functionality in the Lens overlay.

Name: kAndroidOpenPdfInline
Documentation: Enable open PDF inline on Android.

Name: kOsAdditionalSecurityPermissionKillSwitch
Documentation:
When the kill switch is unset, some Chrome features such as
Javascript-Optimizers are gated on an additional OS-provided security
permission. When the kill switch is set, the OS-provided security permission
is ignored when determining whether to enable Chrome features such as
Javascript-Optimizers.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformFeedSegmentFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling Feed user segments feature.

Name: kSeaPenUseProdServer
Documentation: Enables SeaPen Prod Server

Name: kFallbackAfterDecodeError
Documentation:
Falls back to other decoders after audio/video decode error happens. The
implementation may choose different strategies on when to fallback. See
DecoderStream for details. When disabled, playback will fail immediately
after a decode error happens. This can be useful in debugging and testing
because the behavior is simpler and more predictable.

Name: kUseChimeAndroidSdk
Documentation: The feature flag to determine whether to use Chime Android SDK.

Name: kIsolatedWebAppDevMode
Documentation: LINT.IfChange

Name: kLCPPDeferUnusedPreload
Documentation: If enabled, unused preload requests are deferred to the timing on LCP.

Name: kAutofillCapturedSiteTestsMetricsScraper
Documentation:
Testing tool that collects metrics during a run of the captured site tests
and dumps the collected metrics into a specified output directory.
For each test, a file named {test-name}.txt is created. It contains all the
collected metrics in the following format.
histogram-name-1
bucket value
...
histogram-name-2
...
The set of metrics can be restricted using
`kAutofillCapturedSiteTestsMetricsScraperMetricNames`.
It is helpful in conjunction with `tools/captured_sites/metrics-scraper.py`.

Name: kNonUserVisibleDebug
Documentation:
Enables debug info in non-user-visible surfaces, like Chrome Inspector.
Does nothing if `kJourneys` is disabled.

Name: kGooglePlayProtectInApkTelemetry
Documentation: Whether to provide Google Play Protect status in APK telemetry pings

Name: kAutofillLogToTerminal
Documentation: Enables logging the content of chrome://autofill-internals to the terminal.

Name: kVulkan
Documentation:
Enable Vulkan graphics backend for compositing and rasterization. Defaults to
native implementation if --use-vulkan flag is not used. Otherwise
--use-vulkan will be followed.
Note Android WebView uses kWebViewDrawFunctorUsesVulkan instead of this.

Name: kProcessHtmlDataImmediately
Documentation:
If set, HTMLDocumentParser processes data immediately rather than after a
delay. This is further controlled by the feature params starting with the
same name. Also note that this only applies to uses that are normally
deferred (for example, when HTMLDocumentParser is created for inner-html it
is not deferred).

Name: kRequestStorageAccessNoCorsRequired
Documentation:
When enabled, requestStorageAccessFor will require storage access permissions
granted by StorageAccessApi or StorageAccessHeaders to send cookies on
requests allowed because of requestStorageAccessFor instead of cors.

Name: kUseMapRectForPixelMovement
Documentation: Kill switch for using MapRect() to compute filter pixel movement.

Name: kPrefetchUseContentRefactor
Documentation:
This feature was used to launch the prefetch migration from embedder layer to
content/, and this work has finished and the old implemnetation was deleted.
Now this flag is just for injecting parameters through field trials as an
umberella feature.

Name: kJavaScriptRegExpModifiers
Documentation: Enables the RegExp modifiers proposal.

Name: kContentLanguagesInLanguagePicker
Documentation:
This feature enables showing the user's content languages separately at the
top of the language picker menu in the Translate UI.

Name: kFluentOverlayScrollbar
Documentation:
Makes all native scrollbars behave as overlay scrollbars styled to fit the
Fluent design language.
TODO(crbug.com/40280779): Right now this feature flag will force Fluent
overlay scrollbars on. We have yet to decide how we will expose this feature
once it is complete.

Name: kSafeBrowsingDailyPhishingReportsLimit
Documentation:
Enables client side phishing daily reports limit to be configured via Finch
for ESB and SBER users

Name: kEnableBandASampleDebugReports
Documentation:
Enable parsing forDebuggingOnly reports from B&A response. B&A sends these
reports back to Chrome in its response for (1) device orchestrated multi
seller auctions, (2) fDO down sampling.
This flag name is confusing because it controls whether Chrome will parse fDO
reports from B&A, not about whether enabling fDO sampling on B&A. But since
this flag has been enabled by default and will be removed after one Chrome
version, so not worth renaming it which may affect B&A's end to end test.

Name: kWebRtcHideLocalIpsWithMdns
Documentation:
Causes WebRTC to replace host ICE candidate IP addresses with generated
names ending in ".local" and resolve them using mDNS.
http://crbug.com/878465

Name: kKeywordTableHashVerification
Documentation:
An emergency 'off switch' to disable hash verification.
TODO(crbug.com/376303929): Remove in M134.

Name: kRecordBackForwardCacheMetricsWithoutEnabling
Documentation:
This feature is used to limit the scope of back-forward cache experiment
without enabling it. To control the URLs list by using this feature by
generating the metrics only for "allowed_websites" param. Mainly, to ensure
that metrics from the control and experiment groups are consistent.

Name: kSmartZoom
Documentation:
Allows the use of "Smart Zoom", an alternative form of page zoom, and
enables the associated UI.

Name: kSearchEngineChoiceTrigger
Documentation:
Enables the search engine choice screen. Feature parameters below can
affect the actual triggering logic.
The default feature state is split by platform to ease potential merges
that could be needed if we need to change the state while waterfalling this
feature.

Name: kEventStorageManager
Documentation: Controls whether the new storage manager is used to manage events.

Name: kDeviceBoundSessionAccessObserverSharedRemote
Documentation:
When enabled, a shared remote Mojo interface of
DeviceBoundSessionAccessObserver is used to reduce Clone() IPC.
See https://crbug.com/407680127 for more details.

Name: kFileSystemUrlNavigation
Documentation:
Switch to temporary turn back on file system url navigation.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1332598): Remove this feature.

Name: kNtpModulesLoadTimeoutMilliseconds
Documentation:
Dummy feature to set param "NtpModulesLoadTimeoutMillisecondsParam".
This is used for an emergency Finch param. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kRequestSystemAudioFocus
Documentation:
When enabled, Playing media sessions will request audio focus from the
Android system.

Name: kPreventDuplicateImageDecodes
Documentation:
When enabled, and an image decode is requested by both a tile task and
explicitly via img.decode(), it will be decoded only once.

Name: kPartitionAllocSortSmallerSlotSpanFreeLists
Documentation: Whether to sort free lists for smaller slot spans in PurgeMemory().

Name: kFileSystemAccessObserverQuotaLimit
Documentation:
When enabled, sites are limited in how much underlying operating resources
they can access through the `FileSystemObserver` API. This limit is called
the quota limit. Without this enabled, sites will be limited by the system
limit.

Name: kApnPolicies
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file. If a feature is
being rolled out via Finch, add a comment in the .cc file.

Name: kPreserveDiscardableImageMapQuality
Documentation:
When enabled, image quality settings will be preserved in the discardable
image map.

Name: kPrivacySandboxSentimentSurvey
Documentation: Enables the `Always on` sentiment survey

Name: kDisablePEHNotifications
Documentation: Forces the PEH to never show notifications.

Name: kAutofillShowTypePredictions
Documentation:
Controls attaching the autofill type predictions to their respective
element in the DOM.

Name: kPreloadTopChromeWebUILessNavigations
Documentation: An experiment to reduce the number of navigations when preloading WebUIs.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformURLVisitResumptionRanker
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling the URL visit resumption ranker.

Name: kPlatformAudioEncoder
Documentation: Allows usage of OS-level (platform) audio encoders.

Name: kUseNewEtc1Encoder
Documentation: Enables the new ETC1 encoder (used in tab and back/forward thumbnails).

Name: kPassageEmbedder
Documentation:
Used for creating `EmbedderService` and passage extraction in tab helper.
It also hold the feature params used by `PassageEmbeddingsService` to run the
passage embedder, but does not switch it off.

Name: kShopCard
Documentation:
ShopCard in Magic Stack, including shopping features like price drop,
reviews, etc.

Name: kEnableManagementPromotionBanner
Documentation: Feature for the promotion banner on the top of chrome://management page

Name: kEnterpriseRealtimeEventReportingOnIOS
Documentation: Controls whether the realtime events reporting is enabled on iOS.

Name: kUrlScoringModel
Documentation:
If enabled, creates Omnibox autocomplete URL scoring model. Prerequisite for
`kMlUrlScoring` & `kMlUrlSearchBlending`.

Name: kBrokerModelSessionsForUntrustedProcesses
Documentation: Whether model sessions may be brokered to untrusted processes.

Name: kNtpPhotosModule
Documentation: If enabled, Google Photos module will be shown.

Name: kLensOverlaySidePanelOpenInNewTab
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay side panel open in new tab option.

Name: kJourneys
Documentation:
Enables Journeys in the Chrome History WebUI. This flag shouldn't be checked
directly. Instead use `IsJourneysEnabled()` for the system language filter.

Name: kShouldKillSessionOnAcceptChMalformed
Documentation: Whether to kill the session on Error::kAcceptChMalformed.

Name: kWebRtcIgnoreUnspecifiedColorSpace
Documentation:
Causes WebRTC to not set the color space of video frames on the receive side
in case it's unspecified. Otherwise we will guess that the color space is
BT709. http://crbug.com/1129243

Name: kZeroSuggestPrefetching
Documentation: Enables prefetching of the zero prefix suggestions for eligible users on NTP.

Name: kBoostRenderProcessForLoading
Documentation:
If enabled, force renderer process foregrounded from CommitNavigation to
DOMContentLoad (crbug/351953350).

Name: kUmaBackgroundSessions
Documentation: If enabled, keep logging and reporting UMA while chrome is backgrounded.

Name: kHandleOverlaysSwapFailure
Documentation:
This feature allows viz to handle overlays' swap failures instead of loosing a context and
restarting a gpu service.

Name: kAutofillDetectFieldVisibility
Documentation:
If enabled, FormFieldData::is_visible is a heuristic for actual visibility.
Otherwise, it's an alias for FormFieldData::is_focusable.
TODO(crbug.com/324199622) When abandoned, remove FormFieldData::is_visible.

Name: kEnableTabMuting
Documentation: Enables user control over muting tab audio from the tab strip.

Name: kForceHighPerformanceGPUForWebGL
Documentation:
Forces the attribute powerPreference to be set to "high-performance" for
WebGL contexts.

Name: kWebViewPrefetchHighestPrefetchPriority
Documentation: Apply `PrefetchPriority::kHighest` for Webview Prefetch API.

Name: kTriggerPasswordResyncAfterDeletingUndecryptablePasswords
Documentation:
Starts passwords resync after undecryptable passwords were removed. This flag
is enabled by default and should be treaded as a killswitch.

Name: kFledgeTextConversionHelpers
Documentation: Provide encodeUtf8/decodeUtf8 helpers.

Name: kSyncPointGraphValidation
Documentation:
When this flag is enabled, stops using gpu::SyncPointOrderData for sync point
validation, uses gpu::TaskGraph instead.
Graph-based validation doesn't require sync point releases are submitted to
the scheduler prior to their corresponding waits. Therefore it allows to
remove the synchronous flush done by VerifySyncTokens().

TODO(b/324276400): Work in progress.

Name: kAutofillEnableBuyNowPayLaterSyncingForKlarna
Documentation:
When enabled, buy now pay later (BNPL) data for Klarna will be synced to
Chrome clients.

Name: kWebApkInstallFailureNotification
Documentation: Enables WebAPK Install Failure Notification.

Name: kShouldFreezeSelf
Documentation: TODO(thiabaud): Remove these once we fix the include in about/flags

Name: kSuppressesPrerenderingOnSlowNetwork
Documentation: If enabled, suppresses prerendering on slow network.

Name: kFledgeStoreBandAKeysInDB
Documentation:
Enable storing a retrieving B&A keys for the interest group
database.

Name: kPrivateStateTokensDevUI
Documentation:
Enables chrome://privacy-sandbox-internals/private-state-tokens DevUI
page. Relies on PrivacySandboxInternalsDevUI also being enabled.

Name: kSimpleCachePrioritizedCaching
Documentation:
If enabled, main frame navigation resources will be prioritized in Simple
Cache. So they will be less likely to be evicted.

Name: kWebRtcRtpScriptTransformerFrameRestrictions
Documentation:
This features enables the restriction that frames sent to an
RTCRtpScriptTransformer's writable must come from the transformer's readable
and must be written in the same order in which they are read. This feature
does not affect streams created with the createEncodedStreams() method, which
never applies this restriction.

Name: kDsePreload2OnPressIncognito
Documentation:
Enables on-press trigger in incognito mode.

Corresponds to `SearchNavigationPrefetch.allow_incognito`.

For more details, see
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1f4dcNYP3O_Ft4yMmC42ETxGC5lM7YF5FDbEgnxUua7M/edit?tab=t.38v8gca76tmi

Name: kBeaconLeakageLogging
Documentation: The feature flag to enable beacon leakage-related logging logic.

Name: kUseAXPositionForDocumentMarkers
Documentation:
Expose document markers on inline text boxes in addition to
static nodes. (Note: This will make it possible for AXPosition in the browser
process to handle document markers, which will be platform agnositc)

Name: kOidcAuthHeaderInterception
Documentation:
Controls whether OIDC interception from navigation auth header instead of the
usual URL params is permitted. This flag only works on Chrome Canary or Dev.

Name: kWebAssemblyBaseline
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly baseline compilation (Liftoff).

Name: kUpdateCompositorForSurfaceControl
Documentation: Actively update the compositor surface when surface control is enabled.

Name: kMigrateSyncingUserToSignedIn
Documentation:
If enabled, eligible users (i.e. those for which Sync-the-feature is active)
are migrated, at browser startup, to the signed-in non-syncing state.

Name: kDisplayWarningDeprecateURNIframesUseFencedFrames
Documentation:
A console warning is shown when the opaque url returned from Protected
Audience/selectUrl is used to navigate an iframe. Since fenced frames are not
going to be enforced for these APIs in the short-medium term, disabling this
warning for now.

Name: kWebBluetooth
Documentation:
Controls whether the Web Bluetooth API is enabled:
https://webbluetoothcg.github.io/web-bluetooth/

Name: kPrivateAggregationDebugReportingIgnoreSiteExceptions
Documentation:
Prevents site-level exceptions from permitting Private Aggregation debug
reporting if third-party cookies are generally blocked.

Name: kBackForwardCacheMemoryControls
Documentation:
BackForwardCacheMemoryControls is enabled only on Android to disable
BackForwardCache for lower memory devices due to memory limitations.

Name: kAutofillEnableCardBenefitsSync
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will show metadata along with other card information
when the virtual card is presented to users.

Name: kFlushPersistentSystemProfileOnWrite
Documentation:
Determines whether to schedule a flush of persistent histogram memory
immediately after writing a system profile to it.

Name: kEnableBandAKAnonEnforcement
Documentation: Enable parsing and using K-Anonymity features for B&A.

Name: kOnDeviceClusteringVisitRanking
Documentation: Specifies how visits within clusters are ranked.

Name: kFreezingOnBatterySaverForTesting
Documentation:
This is the similar to `kFreezingOnBatterySaver`, with some changes to
facilitate testing:
- Pretend that Battery Saver is active even if it's not.
- Pretend that all tabs have high CPU usage in background.

Name: kFledgeLimitSelectableBuyerAndSellerReportingIds
Documentation:
Configures a limit on the number of `selectableBuyerAndSellerReportingIds`
per ad. This is implemented with two parameters, a hard limit and a soft
limit, intended to ensure that interest groups joined or updated before a
reduction in the limit don't immediately become unusable. The hard limit is
enforced both when an interest group is joined or updated, and also anytime
the interest group is deserialized. The soft limit is only enforced when an
interest group is joined or updated. To execute a reduction in the limit, the
soft limit would first be changed to reflect the new value, and only after
the "maximum interest group TTL" amount of time has passed, the hard limit
would be lowered to match. Except during such a reduction, the hard limit and
soft limits should always match. Increases in the limit can be applied to
both the hard and soft limits simultaneously. The hard limit should always be
greater than or equal to the soft limit. For each parameter, a negative value
indicates that that no limit should be enforced.

Name: kLimitCrossOriginNonActivatedPaintHolding
Documentation: Flag guard for fix for crbug.com/40942531.

Name: kFencedFramesEnforceFocus
Documentation: Enables browser-side focus verification when crossing fenced boundaries.

Name: kLensOverlayRecontextualizeOnQuery
Documentation: Enables recontextualizing on each query for the Lens overlay.

Name: kAutofillAiVoteForFormatStringsFromMultipleFields
Documentation:
If enabled, votes for date format strings from multiple fields are uploaded.
For example, <input type=text value=31> <input type=text value=12> <input
type=text value=2025> leads to the format strings DD and D, MM and M, YYYY,
respectively.

Name: kWebRtcAudioSinkUseTimestampAligner
Documentation:
Feature to make WebRtcAudioSink use TimestampAligner to align absolute
capture timestamps. This is disabled by default.

Name: kWebPaymentsExperimentalFeatures
Documentation:
Master toggle for all experimental features that will ship in the next
release.

Name: kSeparateLocalAndAccountSearchEngines
Documentation: If enabled, keeps local and account search engines separate.

Name: kCoopNoopenerAllowPopups
Documentation:
Enables the "noopener-allow-popups" COOP value, which lets a document to
severe its opener relationship with the document that opened it.
https://github.com/whatwg/html/pull/10394

Name: kTranslateOpenSettings
Documentation:
This feature enables opening language settings in a new tab when the user
clicks "Open language settings" in the Translate bubble menu.

Name: kCloneDevToolsConnectionOnlyIfRequested
Documentation:
When enabled, the CORS URL loader will clone the DevTools connection for a
resource request only if the request includes a DevTools request id.

Name: kOptimizeHTMLElementUrls
Documentation:
Optimize URL copies and resolutions by reducing unnecessary URL construction,
and caching the URLs in Document.

Name: kPauseBrowserInitiatedHeavyTrafficForP2P
Documentation:
When kPauseBrowserInitiatedHeavyTrafficForP2P is enabled, then a subset of
the browser initiated traffic may be paused if there is at least one active
P2P connection and the network is estimated to be congested. This feature is
intended to throttle only the browser initiated traffic that is expected to
be heavy (has large request/response sizes) when real time content might be
streaming over an active P2P connection.

Name: kCapturedSurfaceControlKillswitch
Documentation:
This killswitch is distinct from the OT.
It allows us to remotely disable the feature, and get it to stop working even
on sites that are in possession of a valid token. When that happens, all API
calls gated by the killswitch will fail graceully.

Name: kFedCmWithoutWellKnownEnforcement
Documentation: Enables bypassing the well-known file enforcement.

Name: kSiteInstanceGroupsForDataUrls
Documentation:
When enabled, puts subframe data: URLs in a separate SiteInstance in the same
SiteInstanceGroup as the initiator.

Name: kOptimizationGuideProactivePersonalizedHintsFetching
Documentation:
Enables proactively sending GAIA information to the Optimization Guide
Service.

Name: kWebAuthnICloudKeychainForActiveWithDrive
Documentation: Enabled in M118. Remove in or after M121.

Name: kPlusAddressAcceptedFirstTimeCreateSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kGinJavaBridgeMojoSkipClearObjectsOnMainDocumentReady
Documentation:
Skips clearing objects on main document ready. Only has an impact
when gin java bridge is enabled.

Name: kDisableLoadExtensionCommandLineSwitch
Documentation: Disables loading extensions via the `--load-extension` command line switch.

Name: kSubSampleWindowProxyUsageMetrics
Documentation: Subsample a very chatty UKM metric.

Name: kEnablePolicyPromotionBanner
Documentation:
Enable display for the Chrome Enterprise Core promotion banner on
the chrome://policy page.

Name: kForceWebContentsDarkMode
Documentation: Automatically convert light-themed pages to use a Blink-generated dark theme

Name: kNvidiaVpSuperResolution
Documentation: Allow overlay swapchain to use NVIDIA video processor for super resolution.

Name: kOmniboxMobileParityUpdateV2
Documentation:
Updates various NTP/Omnibox assets and descriptions for visual alignment on
Android and iOS, V2.

Name: kWebRtcCombinedNetworkAndWorkerThread
Documentation: Combine WebRTC Network and Worker threads. More info at crbug.com/1373439.

Name: kSuppressesLoadingPredictorOnSlowNetwork
Documentation: If enabled, suppresses LoadingPredictor (https://crbug.com/350519234)

Name: kVisitedURLRankingScoreThreshold
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling use of score threshold for filtering visits.

Name: kNoPasswordSuggestionFiltering
Documentation: Removes password suggestion filtering by username.

Name: kUseAndroidBufferedInputDispatch
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome will receive buffered/batched input from Android.
Specifically, Chrome will NOT call
https://developer.android.com/reference/kotlin/android/view/View#requestunbuffereddispatch.
If |kInputOnViz| is also enabled, Chrome will call
https://developer.android.com/ndk/reference/group/native-activity#ainputreceiver_createbatchedinputreceiver
instead of the default
https://developer.android.com/ndk/reference/group/native-activity#ainputreceiver_createunbatchedinputreceiver.

Name: kExtensionBrowserNamespaceAlternative
Documentation:
Creates a `browser` object that can be used in place of `chrome` where
extension APIs are available. It does not include non-extension APIs like
`loadTimes` , `csi`, etc. or deprecated APIs (e.g. `app`).

Name: kPseudoMetricsEffectFeature
Documentation:
Used to assess the reliability of field trial data by injecting different
levels of effects to pseudo metrics. These pseudo metrics are just mirrors of
some existing metrics.

Name: kDeleteOverwrittenDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete downloads that are overwritten by others.

Name: kDefaultANGLEVulkan
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's Vulkan backend.

Name: kDisableExtensionsOnChromeUrlsSwitch
Documentation:
Disables the `--extensions-on-chrome-urls` flag's functionality on
`chrome://` URLs. Extension can still run on extension URLs using the new
flag `--extensions-on-extension-urls` flag.

Name: kAutofillDeduplicateAccountAddresses
Documentation:
Feature flag controlling the deduplication of GAS addresses. When disabled
GAS addresses will never be deleted as part of the deduplication flow.
TODO(crbug.com/357074792): Remove when launched.

Name: kRefreshFeedOnRestart
Documentation: Feature that enables refreshing feed when Chrome restarts.

Name: kSyncBookmarksBatchUploadSelectedItems
Documentation:
If enabled, support displaying and uploading individual items (bookmarks or
folders) in the Batch Upload UI.

Batch Upload of all items is supported regardless of this feature flag.

On Windows/Mac/Linux: this flag only affects behavior if the
`switches::kSyncEnableBookmarksInTransportMode` feature is also enabled.

On Android: this flag does not affect user-visiable behavior, but does enable
new code paths.

Name: kBFCachePerformanceManagerPolicy
Documentation:
Policy that evicts the BFCache of pages that become non visible or the
BFCache of all pages when the system is under memory pressure.

Name: kWebViewVulkanIntermediateBuffer
Documentation:
Used to debug Android WebView Vulkan composite. Composite to an intermediate
buffer and draw the intermediate buffer to the secondary command buffer.

Name: kUIDebugTools
Documentation: Enables UI debugging tools such as shortcuts.

Name: kSafetyHubAndroidOrganicSurvey
Documentation: Enables Safety Hub organic HaTS survey on Android.

Name: kUseActivityManagerForTabActivation
Documentation: Activate tab with moveTaskToFront() which works in multi-window mode.

Name: kFileSystemUrlNavigationForChromeAppsOnly
Documentation:
TODO(https://crbug.com/1360512): this feature creates a carveout for
enabling filesystem: URL navigation within Chrome Apps regardless of whether
kFileSystemUrlNavigation is enabled or not.

Name: KScrimForTabModal
Documentation:
When enabled, a scrim is shown behind tab modal dialogs to cover the content
area. This gives user a visual cue that the content area is not interactable.

Name: kBoostImagePriority
Documentation:
Boost the priority of the first N not-small images.
crbug.com/1431169

Name: kOpaqueResponseBlockingErrorsForAllFetches
Documentation:
Treat ORB blocked responses to script-initiated fetches as errors too.
Complements ORB v0.2, which exempts script-initiated fetches.
Implementing ORB in Chromium is tracked in https://crbug.com/1178928

Name: kUACHOverrideBlank
Documentation:
Changes behavior of User-Agent Client Hints to send blank headers when the
User-Agent string is overridden, instead of disabling the headers altogether.

Name: kPrefetchCookieIndices
Documentation:
If enabled, responses with an operative Cookie-Indices will not be used
if the relevant cookie values have changed.

Name: kGlobalVaapiLock
Documentation:
Enable global VA-API lock. Disable this to use lock-free VA-API function
calls for thread safe backends.

Name: kSafelistFTPToRegisterProtocolHandler
Documentation:
When enabled, it adds FTP / FTPS / SFTP to the safe list for
registerProtocolHandler. This feature is enabled by default and meant to
be used as a killswitch.
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/system-state.html#safelisted-scheme

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkersWarningOnly
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks in warning mode for all types of web
workers.

Does nothing if `kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkers` is disabled.

If both this and `kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkers` are enabled, then PNA
preflight requests for workers are not required to succeed. If one fails, a
warning is simply displayed in DevTools.

Name: kAutofillEnableMultipleRequestInVirtualCardDownstreamEnrollment
Documentation:
When enabled, virtual card downstream enrollment will support multiple
requests at a time.

Name: kLCPScriptObserver
Documentation:
If enabled, script execution is observed to determine script dependencies of
the LCP element.

Name: kPrefetchServiceWorkerNoFetchHandlerFix
Documentation:
Fix for prefetching a URL controlled by a ServiceWorker without fetch
handler. Currently this stops prefetching for such cases
(https://crbug.com/379076354).
Even when `kPrefetchServiceWorker` is enabled, this is still effective for
SW-ineligible prefetches.

Name: kWebAppBorderless
Documentation: Enable borderless mode for desktop PWAs. go/borderless-mode

Name: kAutofillPageLanguageDetection
Documentation:
Enables detection of language from Translate.
TODO(crbug.com/40158074): Cleanup when launched.

Name: kImageService
Documentation: Enabled by default because we are only using this as a killswitch.

Name: kPwaUpdateDialogForIcon
Documentation: Shows a confirmation dialog when updates to a PWAs icon has been detected.

Name: kWebUIInProcessResourceLoading
Documentation: Enables in-process resource loading for WebUI renderer processes.

Name: kDocumentPictureInPictureCapture
Documentation: Allows document picture-in-picture pages to request capture.

Name: kClearPipCachedBoundsWhenPermissionPromptVisible
Documentation:
Safety switch to allow us to revert to the previous behavior of using the
cached bounds when the permission prompt is visible. If this feature is
enabled (the default), we will clear the cached bounds, whenever the
permission prompt is visible.

Name: kWebRtcAllowInputVolumeAdjustment
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/40872787): Deactivate the flag gradually before deleting it.
When disabled, any WebRTC Audio Processing Module input volume recommendation
is ignored and no adjustment takes place.

Name: kAutofillDisableAddressImport
Documentation: Kill switch for Autofill address import.

Name: kSplitCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Splits cache entries by the request's NetworkIsolationKey if one is
available.

Name: kReclaimOldPrepaintTiles
Documentation:
When enabled, old prepaint tiles in the "eventually" region get reclaimed
after some time.

Name: kNavigationNetworkResponseQueue
Documentation:
When NavigationNetworkResponseQueue is enabled, the browser will schedule
some tasks related to navigation network responses in a kHigh priority
queue.

Name: kSqlFixedMmapSize
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kKeepDefaultSearchEngineRendererAlive
Documentation:
When enabled, keep the default search engine render process host alive
(crbug.com/365958798).

Name: kNoticeFrameworkTopicsApiFeature
Documentation: Api Features

Name: kWebRtcApm48kHzSampleRateOnAndroidKillSwitch
Documentation:
Kill-switch for using 48 kHz as sample rate for Audio Processing Module
processing on Android. When enabled, enforces a 16 kHz sample rate for audio
processing on Android.

Name: kEnforceSHA256Checking
Documentation:
Enforce the use of SHA256 digest for signatures.
If disabled, the device may respond with a signature with SHA1 digest even
though a signature with SHA256 digest was requested in the challenge. This
allows for backwards compatibility with legacy Cast receivers.

Name: kAlpsForHttp2
Documentation:
Enables ALPS extension of TLS 1.3 for HTTP/2, see
https://vasilvv.github.io/tls-alps/draft-vvv-tls-alps.html and
https://vasilvv.github.io/httpbis-alps/draft-vvv-httpbis-alps.html.

Name: kFeedFollowUiUpdate
Documentation: Feature that enables UI update for Follow.

Name: kPermissionsPromptSurvey
Documentation:
Controls whether to trigger showing a HaTS survey, with the given
`probability` and `trigger_id`. The `probability` parameter is defined and
handled by the HatsService itself. If the parameter
`kPermissionsPromptSurveyDisplayTime` is set to `OnPromptResolved` (default),
the survey is shown immediately after the user has taken the action specified
in `action_filter` on a permission prompt for the capability specified in
`request_type_filter`. If, on the other hand, the
`kPermissionsPromptSurveyDisplayTime` is set to `OnPromptAppearing`, the
survey is shown when the prompt is first shown to the user. Note, that
configuring `PermissionAction` does not make sense in that case, since the
user has not yet taken an action. Therefore, that parameter is ignored in
that case.

Name: kThrottleDelayable
Documentation:
Based on the field trial parameters, this feature will override the value of
the maximum number of delayable requests allowed in flight. The number of
delayable requests allowed in flight will be based on the network's
effective connection type ranges and the
corresponding number of delayable requests in flight specified in the
experiment configuration. Based on field trial parameters, this experiment
may also throttle delayable requests based on the number of non-delayable
requests in-flight times a weighting factor.

Name: kThirdPartyPartitionedStorageAllowedByDefault
Documentation:
When enabled, partitioned storage will be allowed even if third-party cookies
are disabled by default. Partitioned storage will not be allowed if
third-party cookies are disabled due to a specific rule.

Name: kEnableEarlyHintsOnHttp11
Documentation: Enables Early Hints on HTTP/1.1.

Name: kAutofillEnableAblationStudy
Documentation:
Controls an ablation study in which autofill for addresses and payment data
can be suppressed.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformIntentionalUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling intentional user segment.

Name: kEnableAdditionalTextMetrics
Documentation: A kill switch for additional metrics added to ComposeTextUsageLogger.

Name: kAttachUnownedInnerWebContents
Documentation:
Whether to allow attaching an inner WebContents not owned by the outer
WebContents. This is for prototyping purposes and should not be enabled in
production.

Name: kPrewarm
Documentation: DSE Prewarm tracked at https://crbug.com/406378765.

Name: kEncryptAllPasswordsWithOSCryptAsync
Documentation:
Enables re-encryption of all passwords. Done separately for each store
(Stage 3).

Name: kLCPPMultipleKey
Documentation: If enabled, LCPP learns with additional first-level-path key to origin.

Name: kStaticStorageQuota
Documentation: A kill switch for the new reported quota being a static value.

Name: kWebAuthnHelloSignal
Documentation: Enables the WebAuthn Signal API for Windows Hello.

Name: kWebUSBTransferSizeLimit
Documentation: Kill switch for https://crbug.com/338955051.

Name: kNtpMicrosoftAuthenticationModule
Documentation: If enabled, the Microsoft Authentication module will be shown.

Name: kShowEnterpriseDialogForAllManagedAccountsSignin
Documentation:
Enables showing the enterprise dialog after every signin into a managed
account.

Name: kAutofillExtractOnlyNonAdFrames
Documentation:
If enabled, only non-ad frames are extracted.
Otherwise, non-ad frames as well as *visible* ad frames are extracted.
"Extracted" means that FormFieldData::child_frames is populated, which is
necessary for flattening these forms.
The forms in those frames are extracted either way.
TODO(crbug.com/40196220): Remove once launched.

Name: kAutofillThirdPartyModeContentProvider
Documentation:
If enabled, Autofill Services can query whether Chrome provides forms as
virtual view structures to third party providers.

Name: kSafetyHubFollowup
Documentation: Enables Safety Hub followup work.

Name: kOidcEnrollmentTimeout
Documentation: Controls whether OIDC enrollment process can time out (and after how long).

Name: kHideSuggestionGroupHeaders
Documentation:
If enabled, suggestion group headers in the Omnibox popup will be hidden
(e.g. in order to minimize visual clutter in the zero-prefix state).

Name: kWebSerialBlocklist
Documentation:
Feature used to configure entries in the Web Serial API blocklist which can
be deployed using a server configuration.

Name: kFledgeLimitNumAuctions
Documentation:
If enabled, limits the number of FLEDGE auctions that can be run between page
load and unload -- any attempt to run more than this number of auctions will
fail (return null to JavaScript).

Name: kWebAuthnMicrosoftSoftwareUnexportableKeyProvider
Documentation:
Enables using the Microsoft Software Key Storage Provider to store
unexportable keys when a TPM is not available.

Name: kAutofillUploadThrottling
Documentation:
Autofill upload throttling limits uploading a form to the Autofill server
more than once over a `kAutofillUploadThrottlingPeriodInDays` period.
This feature is for testing purposes and is not supposed
to be launched.

Name: kRecordWebAppDebugInfo
Documentation:
Enables recording additional web app related debugging data to be displayed
in: chrome://web-app-internals

Name: kUseItemSnippetsAPI
Documentation: If enabled, use the new CWS itemSnippets API to fetch extension info.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAdsApiUxEnhancements
Documentation: If true, displays the Ads APIs UX Enancements.

Name: kWebIdentityDigitalCredentialsCreation
Documentation: Enables the Digital Credentials Creation API.

Name: kSandboxExternalProtocolBlockedWarning
Documentation: Enabled in M100. Flag to be removed in M106

Name: kBackForwardCacheSize
Documentation:
Allows overriding the sizes of back/forward cache.
Sizes set via this feature's parameters take precedence over others.
Enables BackForwardCache size for
 - desktop: https://crbug.com/1291435.
 - android: https://crbug.com/1395281.

Name: kUkmReduceAddEntryIPC
Documentation:
This feature controls whether MojoUkmRecorder gets to decide whether to send
an IPC for AddEntry.

Name: kLensOverlayEduActionChip
Documentation: Enables the EDU action chip.

Name: kPrefetchFontLookupTables
Documentation: If enabled, font lookup tables will be prefetched on renderer startup.

Name: kMediaDrmGetStatusForPolicy
Documentation:
Enables MediaDrmBridge to call into MediaDrm API to query HDCP Status to
support the CDM API GetStatusForPolicy.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAllowPromptForBlocked3PCookies
Documentation: If true, will not block prompt when third party cookies are blocked.

Name: kFledgeUseKVv2SignalsCache
Documentation:
Enables using a cache in the browser process for FLEDGE KVv2 fetches. The
fetches are also initiated by and managed in the browser process. This
feature also requires blink::features::kFledgeTrustedSignalsKVv2Support to
also be enabled for KVv2 to be enabled.

Name: kAllowDownloadResumptionWithoutStrongValidators
Documentation: Whether download resumption is allowed when there are no strong validators.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformAndroidHomeModuleRanker
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling android home module ranker.

Name: kLensSearchSidePanelNewFeedback
Documentation: Enables a new feedback entrypoint in the Lens side panel.

Name: kWebAuthnPasskeyUpgrade
Documentation: Enable passkey upgrade requests in Google Password Manager.

Name: kUseHostResolverCache
Documentation:
If enabled, HostResolver will use the new HostResolverCache that separately
caches by DNS type, unlike the old HostCache that always cached by merged
request results. May enable related behavior such as separately sorting DNS
results after each transaction rather than sorting collectively after all
transactions complete.

Name: kProtectedAudienceCorsSafelistKVv2Signals
Documentation:
Enables CORS safelisting the Protected Audience Trusted Key-Value
Content-Type.

Name: kBackgroundFetch
Documentation: Kill switch for Background Fetch.

Name: kDeclarativeNetRequestSafeRuleLimits
Documentation:
Enables a relaxed rule count for "safe" dynamic or session scoped rules above
the current limit. If disabled, all dynamic and session scoped rules are
treated as "safe" but the rule limit's value will be the stricter "unsafe"
limit.

Name: kBiometricAuthIdentityCheck
Documentation:
The feature flag for the Identity Check feature. The feature makes biometric
authentication mandatory before password filling in untrusted locations.

Name: kServiceWorkerStaticRouterRaceNetworkRequestPerformanceImprovement
Documentation:
crbug.com/374606637: When this is enabled, race-network-and-fetch-hander will
prioritize the response processing for the network request over the
processing for the fetch handler.

Name: kEnableVariableRefreshRateAlwaysOn
Documentation: Enables the variable refresh rate feature at all times.

Name: kEnableComposeNudgeAtCursor
Documentation: Controls whether or not the nudge displays at the cursor.

Name: kWebRtcHWEncoding
Documentation: Enables HW encode acceleration for WebRTC.

Name: kLensOverlaySuggestionsMigration
Documentation:
Enables the migration for Lens overlay suggestions URL params, independent
of the CSB feature.

Name: kActiveContentSettingExpiry
Documentation:
Lets the HostContentSettingsMap actively monitor when content settings expire
and delete them instantly. This also notifies observers that will, in turn,
terminate access to capabilities gated on those settings right away.

Name: kLCPPPrefetchSubresourceAsync
Documentation: If enabled, doing prefetch task async after main resource fetching.

Name: kSplitAuthCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Enables or defaults splittup up server (not proxy) entries in the
HttpAuthCache.

Name: kWebCodecsVideoEncoderFrameDrop
Documentation: A video encoder is allowed to drop a frame in WebCodecs.

Name: kDeviceBoundSessionTerminationEvictBackForwardCache
Documentation:
When a device bound session
(https://github.com/w3c/webappsec-dbsc/blob/main/README.md) is
terminated, evict pages with cache-control:no-store from the
BFCache. Note that if `kCacheControlNoStoreEnterBackForwardCache` is
disabled, no such pages will be in the cache.

Name: kWebViewEnableADPF
Documentation:
If enabled and the device's SOC manufacturer satisifes the allowlist and
blocklist rules, WebView reports the set of threads involved in frame
production to HWUI, and they're included in the HWUI ADPF session.
If disabled, WebView never uses ADPF.
The allowlist takes precedence - i.e. if the allowlist is non-empty, the
soc must be in the allowlist for WebView to use ADPF, and the blocklist is
ignored. If there's no allowlist, the soc must be absent from the blocklist.

Name: kRecordWebAudioEngagement
Documentation: Enables Media Engagement Index recording for Web Audio playbacks.

Name: kApiUserScriptsExecute
Documentation:
Controls the availability of executing user scripts programmatically using
the userScripts API.

Name: kEnableComposeSelectionNudge
Documentation: Controls whether or not the nudge should be shown on text selection.

Name: kKeyboardAccessibleTooltip
Documentation:
Used to enable keyboard accessible tooltips in in-page content
(i.e., inside Blink). See
::views::features::kKeyboardAccessibleTooltipInViews for
keyboard-accessible tooltips in Views UI.

Name: kAccountForSuppressedKeyboardInsets
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kSafeBrowsingSubresourceFilter
Documentation: The primary toggle to enable/disable the Safe Browsing Subresource Filter.

Name: kAutofillEnableBuyNowPayLaterSyncing
Documentation: When enabled, buy now pay later (BNPL) data will be synced to Chrome clients.

Name: kCanvasNoise
Documentation:
Whether the canvas interventions should be enabled that add noise to the
readback values.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkers
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks for all types of web workers.

This affects initial worker script fetches, fetches initiated by workers
themselves, and service worker update fetches.

The exact checks run are the same as for other document subresources, and
depend on the state of other Private Network Access feature flags:

 - `kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessRespectPreflightResults`

Name: kAutofillUpstream
Documentation:
Controls offering credit card upload to Google Payments. Cannot ever be
ENABLED_BY_DEFAULT because the feature state depends on the user's country.
The set of launched countries is listed in autofill_experiments.cc, and this
flag remains as a way to easily enable upload credit card save for testers,
as well as enable non-fully-launched countries on a trial basis.

Name: kDisablePhotoPickerForVideoCapture
Documentation: Whether photo picker should be disabled for video capture.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromPrivate
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, requests to localhost initiated from non-secure
contexts in the `private` IP address space are blocked.

See also:
 - https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#integration-fetch
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests

Name: kLinkedServicesSetting
Documentation:
Defines if the linked services setting is eligible to be shown in Chrome
settings.

Name: kEnableClipboardDataControlsAndroid
Documentation: Controls enabling Data Controls rules for clipboard copy / paste on Android.

Name: kAutofillReplaceFormElementObserver
Documentation:
Replaces blink::WebFormElementObserver usage in FormTracker by updated logic
for tracking the disappearance of forms as well as other submission
triggering events.
TODO(crbug.com/40281981): Remove when launched.

Name: kComposeAXSnapshot
Documentation: Enables/disables inner text context gathering.

Name: kTpcdMetadataStageControl
Documentation: Whether to enable staged rollback of the TPCD Metadata Entries.

Name: kNtpWallpaperSearchButtonAnimationShownThreshold
Documentation:
Dummy feature to set param "NtpWallpaperSearchButtonAnimationShownThreshold".
This is used for an emergency Finch param. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformTabResumptionRanker
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling tab resumption ranker.

Name: kMediaCodecElideEOS
Documentation: Allow EOS buffers to be elided by MediaCodecVideoDecoder.

Name: kImageServiceOptimizationGuideSalientImages
Documentation: Enabled the capability by default, can be used as a killswitch.

Name: kPeriodicBackgroundSync
Documentation: Whether web apps can run periodic tasks upon network connectivity.

Name: kHappyEyeballsV3
Documentation:
Enables the Happy Eyeballs v3, where we use intermediate DNS resolution
results to make connection attempts as soon as possible.

Name: kClearUndecryptablePasswords
Documentation: Delete undecryptable passwords from the login database.

Name: kCrossOriginOpenerPolicyByDefault
Documentation:
Shift's COOP's default from `unsafe-none` to `same-origin-allow-popups`.
https://github.com/mikewest/coop-by-default/

Name: kCompressionDictionaryTransportOverHttp2
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, Chromium can use stored shared dictionaries
even when the connection is using HTTP/2 for non-localhost requests.

Name: kOverscrollBehaviorRespectedOnAllScrollContainers
Documentation:
When enabled, the overscroll behavior will be respected on all scroll
containers.

Name: kSuspiciousSiteTriggerQuotaFeature
Documentation: Controls the daily quota for the suspicious site trigger.

Name: kLensSearchNotFoundOnPageToast
Documentation:
Enables the search not found on page toast when a user clicks a citation for
the current page they are viewing but the text was not found.

Name: kComposeEligible
Documentation: Force compose off even if enabled by other switches..

Name: kPausePagesPerBrowsingContextGroup
Documentation:
When enabled, only pages that belong to a certain browsing context group are
paused instead of all pages.

Name: kSamplingProfilerReporting
Documentation: base::Feature for reporting CPU profiles. Provided here for test use.

Name: kOriginAgentClusterDefaultEnabled
Documentation:
If enabled, an absent Origin-Agent-Cluster: header is interpreted as
requesting an origin agent cluster, but in the same process.

Name: kV8CompactWithStack
Documentation: Enable compaction when finalizing a full GC with stack.

Name: kForceSafeSearchForUnauthenticatedSupervisedUsers
Documentation:
Force enable SafeSearch for a supervised profile with an
unauthenticated (e.g. signed out of the content area) account.

Name: kProtectedAudienceMeasurementNoticeModalFeature
Documentation: EEA Notice Features

Name: kEnforceNoopenerOnBlobURLNavigation
Documentation:
Prevents an opener from being returned when a BlobURL is cross-site to the
window's top-level site.

Name: kSafetyHubWeakAndReusedPasswords
Documentation: Enables Weak and Reused passwords in Safety Hub.

Name: kHeapProfilerReporting
Documentation:
If this is disabled, the client will not collect heap profiles. If it is
enabled, the client may enable the sampling heap profiler (with probability
based on the "stable-probability" parameter if the client is on the stable
channel, or the "nonstable-probability" parameter otherwise). Sampled heap
profiles will then be reported through the metrics service iff metrics
reporting is enabled.

Name: kPrerender2WarmUpCompositorForImmediate
Documentation:
If enabled, requests the compositor warm-up (crbug.com/41496019) for
Immediate/non-Immediate Speculation Rules prerenders.

Name: kFledgeTruncateSelectableBuyerAndSellerReportingIdsToKAnonLimit
Documentation:
Feature flag to truncate the set of `selectableBuyerAndSellerReportingIds`
to only those for which k-anon status was fetched, as limited by the
kFledgeSelectableBuyerAndSellerReportingIdsFetchedFromKAnonLimit parameter
defined above.

Name: kExternalAppRedirectTelemetry
Documentation: Enables reporting of external app redirects

Name: kContinueGestureOnLosingFocus
Documentation:
When disabled("legacy behavior") it resets ongoing gestures when window loses
focus. In split screen scenario this means we can't continue scroll on a
chrome window, when we start interacting with another window.

Name: kMerchantTrustLearnSurvey
Documentation:
Enables the 'Merchant trust' sentiment survey that will be available for
users in the page info. Feature params are set directly in the code as due to
finch / fieldtrial config limitations we can't configure multiple surveys
with same params name but different values in distinct features within the
same config group.

Name: kJavaScriptRegExpDuplicateNamedGroups
Documentation: Enables the RegExp duplicate named capture groups proposal.

Name: kSpeakerChangeDetection
Documentation:
Enable the Speaker Change Detection feature, which inserts a line break when
the Speech On-Device API (SODA) detects a speaker change.

Name: kAutofillEnablePrefetchingRiskDataForRetrieval
Documentation:
When enabled, risk data is prefetched during payments autofill flows to
reduce user-perceived latency.

Name: kOledScaleFactorEnabled
Documentation: Enable display scale factor meant for OLED display.

Name: kCctAutoTranslate
Documentation:
This feature enables certain trusted Android apps to open a Chrome Custom Tab
and cause it to immediately automatically translate into a desired target
language.

Name: kEnterpriseProfileBadgingForMenu
Documentation:
Enables enterprise profile badging for managed profiles on the toolbar avatar
and in the profile menu. On managed profiles, a building icon will be used as
a badge in the profile menu.

Name: kIncomingCallNotifications
Documentation:
Enables the Incoming Call Notifications scenario. When created by an
installed origin, an incoming call notification should have increased
priority, colored buttons, a ringtone, and a default "close" button.
Otherwise, if the origin is not installed, it should behave like the default
notifications, but with the added "Close" button. See
https://github.com/MicrosoftEdge/MSEdgeExplainers/blob/main/Notifications/notifications_actions_customization.md

Name: kFreezingOnBatterySaver
Documentation:
When enabled, browsing instances with high CPU usage in background are frozen
when Battery Saver is active. Depends on `kCPUMeasurementInFreezingPolicy`.

Name: kBookmarkTriggerForPrerender2
Documentation:
This flag is used for enabling Bookmark triggered prerendering. See
crbug.com/1422819 for more details of Bookmark triggered prerendering.

Name: kSCTAuditing
Documentation:
This requires backend infrastructure and a data collection policy.
Non-Chrome builds should not use Chrome's infrastructure.

Name: kEnterpriseIframeDlpRulesSupport
Documentation:
Controls whether the iFrame parent url chain initiated from the active frame
will be attached to DLP scan requests.

Name: kSafetyHubLocalPasswordsModule
Documentation: Enables the local passwords module in Safety Hub.

Name: kAutofillAiIgnoreGeoIp
Documentation:
If enabled, no GeoIp requirements are imposed for AutfillAi. Intended for
Dogfood and testing only.

Name: kClientSideDetectionKillswitch
Documentation:
Killswitch for client side phishing detection. Since client side models are
run on a large fraction of navigations, crashes due to the model are very
impactful, even if only a small fraction of users have a bad version of the
model. This Finch flag allows us to remediate long-tail component versions
while we fix the root cause. This will also halt the model distribution from
OptimizationGuide.

Name: kDocumentIsolationPolicy
Documentation:
Enables Document-Isolation-Policy (DIP).
https://github.com/WICG/document-isolation-policy

Name: kFreezingFollowsDiscardOptOut
Documentation:
When enabled, the freezing policy won't freeze pages that are opted out of
tab discarding.

Name: kInternalMediaSession
Documentation:
Enables the internal Media Session logic without enabling the Media Session
service.

Name: kMaskedDomainListFlatbufferImpl
Documentation:
When enabled, if the MaskedDomainList is used at all, it will use the
flatbuffer implementation (the `MaskedDomainList` class) instead of the
`UrlMatcherWithBypass` implementation.

Name: kAutofillSupportLastNamePrefix
Documentation: Enables using custom name model with last name prefixes support.

Name: kRenderDocumentCompositorReuse
Documentation: Reuse compositor instances with RenderDocument

Name: kPostMessageFirstPartyToThirdPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlocked
Documentation:
Whether first-party to third-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked.

Name: kEnableRtcpReporting
Documentation:
Controls whether the Mirroring Service will fetch, analyze, and store
information on the quality of the session using RTCP logs.

Name: kAndroidUseCorrectDisplayWorkArea
Documentation:
Feature controlling how to compute work area on Android.
TODO(crbug.com/372385871): Cleanup flag after investigating nothing is broken
after changing the default behavior for
availWidth/availHeight/availTop/availLeft.

Name: kPasswordFormGroupedAffiliations
Documentation: Enables offering credentials for filling across grouped domains.

Name: kCCSlimming
Documentation:
Kill switch for a bunch of optimizations for cc-slimming project.
Please see crbug.com/335450599 for more details.

Name: kPrivacySandboxSettings4
Documentation: Enables the fourth release of the Privacy Sandbox settings.

Name: kAutofillAiVoteForFormatStringsFromSingleFields
Documentation:
If enabled, votes for date format strings from individual fields are
uploaded. For example, <input type=text value=31/12/2025> leads to the format
strings DD/MM/YYYY and D/M/YYYY.

Name: kAndroidAppIntegrationModule
Documentation:
The maximum number of times the auxiliary search promo card can be visible to
the user.

Name: kJumpStartOmnibox
Documentation:
Accelerates time from cold start to focused Omnibox on low-end devices,
prioritizing Omnibox focus and background initialization.

Name: kTabstripComboButton
Documentation: Controls where tab search lives in the browser.

Name: kAllowContentInitiatedDataUrlNavigations
Documentation: Please keep features in alphabetical order.

Name: kHistoryClustersInternalsPage
Documentation: Enables the history clusters internals page.

Name: kAutofillAndPasswordsInSameSurface
Documentation:
Guards the refactoring to allow showing Autofill and Password suggestions in
the same surface instead of being mutually exclusive.

Name: kResumeBackgroundVideo
Documentation:
Let videos be resumed via remote controls (for example, the notification)
when in background.

Name: kMemoryMeasurementInFreezingPolicy
Documentation:
When enabled, the freezing policy measures memory usage. This exists to
quantify the overhead of memory measurement in a holdback study.

Name: kClientSideDetectionKeyboardPointerLockRequest
Documentation:
Expand CSPP beyond phishing and trigger when keyboard or pointer lock request
occurs on the page.

Name: kExtensionsToolbarZeroState
Documentation:
If enabled, guide users with zero extensions installed to explore the
benefits of extensions.
Displays an IPH anchored to the Extensions Toolbar Button, and replaces the
extensions submenu with an alternative submenu to recommend extensions.

Name: kThreadPoolCap2
Documentation: Fixed amount of threads that will be used as a cap for thread pools.

Name: kAutofillRetryImageFetchOnFailure
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will try to fetch payment account image resources again
upon failure. The number of attempts is a controllable parameter. This is a
kill-switch.
TODO(crbug.com/40276036): Clean up after M139 branch (June 23, 2025).

Name: kEnableBandAClickiness
Documentation: Enable sending clickiness data in B&A requests.

Name: kSkiaGraphite
Documentation:
Enable Skia Graphite. This will use the Dawn backend by default, but can be
overridden with command line flags for testing on non-official developer
builds. See --skia-graphite-backend flag in gpu_switches.h.
Note: This can also be overridden by
--enable-skia-graphite & --disable-skia-graphite.

Name: kSharedHighlightingManager
Documentation: Enables the new SharedHighlightingManager refactoring.

Name: kTpcdMetadataGrants
Documentation:
Whether to enable the use of 3PC based on 3PCD metadata grants delivered via
component updater.

Name: kFedCmIframeOrigin
Documentation:
For cross-site iframes, sends the top-level origin to the IDP and parses
an optional returned boolean indicating whether it is part of the same
client to allow for UI decisions based on the boolean.

Name: kEsbAsASyncedSetting
Documentation:
Makes the Enhanced Protection a syncable setting.
Check the design doc (go/esb-as-a-synced-setting-dd) for further details.

Name: kHttpsFirstDialogUi
Documentation: Enables a dialog-based UI for HTTPS-First Mode.

Name: kFilterInstalledAppsWebAppMatching
Documentation: Enables installed web app matching for getInstalledRelatedApps API.

Name: kImageSearchSuggestionThumbnail
Documentation:
Please do not add more features to this "big blob" list.
Instead, use the categorized and alphabetized lists below this "big blob".
You can create a new category if none of the existing ones fit.

Name: kMbiOverrideTaskRunnerHandle
Documentation:
If enabled, base::SingleThreadTaskRunner::GetCurrentDefault() and
base::SequencedTaskRunner::GetCurrentDefault() returns the current active
per-ASG task runner instead of the per-thread task runner.

Name: kStreamlineRendererInit
Documentation: Reduces the work done during renderer initialization.

Name: kEnableEdidBasedDisplayIds
Documentation:
TODO(gildekel): A temporary flag to control whether EDID-based (vs.
port-based) display IDs are generated per display. Remove once the migration
process it complete (b/193019614).

Name: kMeasurementNoticeModalFeature
Documentation: Restricted Notice Features

Name: kEmulateLoadStartedForInspectorOncePerResource
Documentation:
If enabled, the body of `EmulateLoadStartedForInspector` is executed only
once per Resource per ResourceFetcher, and thus duplicated network load
entries in DevTools caused by `EmulateLoadStartedForInspector` are removed.
https://crbug.com/1502591

Name: kNtpMiddleSlotPromoDismissal
Documentation:
If enabled, middle slot promo will be dismissed from New Tab Page until new
promo message is populated

Name: kAndroidSurfaceControl
Documentation:
Use android SurfaceControl API for managing display compositor's buffer queue
and using overlays on Android. Also used by webview to disable surface
SurfaceControl.

Name: kLastVSyncArgsKillswitch
Documentation:
Stops BeginFrame issue to use |last_vsync_interval_| instead of the current
set of BeginFrameArgs.
TODO(b/333940735): Should be removed if the issue isn't fixed.

Name: kPwaNavigationCapturing
Documentation: Enables user link capturing on all desktop platforms.

Name: kVisitedURLRankingService
Documentation: Core feature flag for Visited URL Ranking service.

Name: kPrerenderMoreCorrectSpeculativeRFHCreation
Documentation:
A misunderstanding when fixing crbug.com/40076091 meant that non-speculative
RFHs were being created with a provisional RenderFrame in the renderer. This
is nominally harmless, but can crash prerenders if devtool's network
overrides feature is enabled. Guarded by a feature since fixing this new bug
might reintroduce the previous crashes.

Name: kDeprecatedExternalPickerFunction
Documentation: Use the old-style opening of an External Picker when uploading files.

Name: kRenderSizeInScoreAdBrowserSignals
Documentation:
Enable the optional renderSize field in the browserSignals parameter of
scoreAd function of Protected Audience API.
See explainer:
https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE.md#23-scoring-bids

Name: kAutofillAcrossIframesIosThrottling
Documentation:
Throttles child frame extraction to a maximum number of child frames that
can be extracted by applying the following rules: (1) remove the child frames
from an individual form that busts the limit and (2) stop extracting child
frames on other forms once the limit is reached across forms.

Name: kContentSettingsPartitioning
Documentation:
Whether we should partition content settings (by StoragePartitions for
non-ios platforms).

Name: kWebAuthnNewBfCacheHandling
Documentation:
With this flag, WebAuthn only disables the back-forward cache during the
lifetime of a WebAuthn request.
With the flag off, the back-forward cache is disabled for the lifetime of
the page when a request is started.

Name: kDataSharingEnableUpdateChromeUI
Documentation:
Feature flag to show UI that prompts the user to update Chrome when the
version is out of date.
Note: Do not clean up this feature as it is meant to be used in unforeseen
situations as a kill switch in future from finch when the shared tab groups
feature becomes incompatible for the current chrome client.

Name: kEnableWebTransportDraft07
Documentation: Enables draft-07 version of WebTransport over HTTP/3.

Name: kDisableTLSResumption
Documentation: Disables TLS resumption.

Name: kGCMAvoidConnectionWhenNetworkUnavailable
Documentation: When enabled, the connection to the server won't be initiated when offline.

Name: kCacheStorageParallelOps
Documentation:
Enables support for parallel cache_storage operations via the
"max_shared_ops" fieldtrial parameter.

Name: kComposeTextOutputAnimation
Documentation: Enables animation of text output. Applies only to on-device evaluation.

Name: kOnDeviceModelValidation
Documentation: Whether the on-device model validation checks are enabled.

Name: kSeparateLocalAndAccountThemes
Documentation: If enabled, distinguishes between local and account themes.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformIosModuleRankerSplitBySurface
Documentation: Feature flag for having separate models for the Start and NTP surface.

Name: kOmniboxDemoteByType
Documentation:
Demotes the relevance scores when comparing suggestions based on the
suggestion's |AutocompleteMatchType| and the user's |PageClassification|.
This feature's main job is to contain the DemoteByType parameter.

Name: kAutofillSyncEwalletAccounts
Documentation:
When enabled, eWallet accounts are synced from the Google Payments servers
and displayed on the payment methods settings page.

Name: kAutofillBetterLocalHeuristicPlaceholderSupport
Documentation:
When enabled, the placeholder is not considered a label fallback on the
renderer side anymore. Instead, local heuristic will match regexes against
either the label or the placeholder, depending on how high quality the label
is. If no matche is found, local heuristics fall back to the other value.
This feature can be thought of as "lightweight" multi-label support.
TODO(crbug.com/320965828): Remove when launched.

Name: kServiceWorkerClientUrlIsCreationUrl
Documentation:
(crbug.com/41337436): Enabled feature will have the ServiceWorker Client.url
property be the creation URL. This means it does not reflect changes to the
URL made by history.pushState() or similar history APIs.
When disabled the ServiceWorker Client.url property will be the document URL
including changes to history.pushState().

Name: kHttpsFirstModeV2ForEngagedSites
Documentation:
Enables HTTPS-First Mode for engaged sites. No-op if HttpsFirstModeV2 or
HTTPS-Upgrades is disabled.

Name: kImageAnnotationServiceExperimental
Documentation: Whether or not to override service parameters for experimentation.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForNavigationsWarningOnly
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks in warning mode for navigations.

Does nothing if `kPrivateNetworkAccessForNavigations` is disabled.

If both this and `kPrivateNetworkAccessForNavigations` are enabled, then PNA
preflight requests for navigations are not required to succeed. If
one fails, a warning is simply displayed in DevTools.

Name: kWebRtcAV1HWEncode
Documentation:
When enabled, allows AV1 HW encoding to be used for WebRTC streams, if the
platform accelerator supports encoding of AV1.

Name: kThemesBatchUpload
Documentation: If enabled, offers batch upload of local themes upon sign in.

Name: kInvalidateSearchEngineChoiceOnDeviceRestoreDetection
Documentation:
Invalidates old search engine choices when Chrome detects that it has been
transferred to a new device.

Name: kPrerender2WarmUpCompositorForBookmarkBar
Documentation:
If enabled, requests the compositor warm-up (crbug.com/41496019) for
each prerender trigger.

Name: kUseLibunwindstackNativeUnwinderAndroid
Documentation:
Use the LibunwindstackNativeUnwinderAndroid for only browser main thread, and
only on Android.

Name: kSafetyHub
Documentation: Enables Safety Hub feature.

Name: kShopCardImpressionLimits
Documentation: Impression limits on ShopCards

Name: kUseAndroidOverlayForSecureOnly
Documentation:
Use AndroidOverlay only if required for secure video playback. This requires
that |kOverlayFullscreenVideo| is true, else it is ignored.

Name: kHttpsFirstModeIncognito
Documentation:
Enables HTTPS-First Mode by default in Incognito Mode. (The related feature
kHttpsFirstModeIncognitoNewSettings controls whether new settings controls
are available for opting out of this default behavior.)

Name: kAccessibilityInlineLineSeparators
Documentation:
When populating the AccessibilityNodeInfo on Android, Clank will insert Line
Separator U+2028 characters in the text to denote soft line breaks.

Name: kOpenAllUrlsOrFilesOnDrop
Documentation: Fix for https://crbug.com/40927333.

Name: kTabGroupSyncDisableNetworkLayer
Documentation:
Feature flag used to determine whether the network layer is disabled for
tab group sync.

Name: kSendCnameAliasesToSubresourceFilterFromRenderer
Documentation:
Performs additional SubresourceFilter checks when CNAME aliases are found
for the host of a requested URL.

Name: kCreateWarningShownClientSafeBrowsingReports
Documentation: Creates and sends CSBRRs when warnings are first shown to users.

Name: kDownloadsPageReferrerUrl
Documentation:
Show referrer URL on download item on chrome://downloads page. This will
replace the downloads url.

Name: kMediaDrmPersistentLicense
Documentation:
An experimental feature to enable persistent-license type support in MediaDrm
when using Encrypted Media Extensions (EME) API.
TODO(xhwang): Remove this after feature launch. See http://crbug.com/493521

Name: kEnableAsyncUploadAfterVerdict
Documentation:
Controls uploading scanned data even after a metadata verdict
is received for content scans.

Name: kBluetoothBtsnoopInternals
Documentation:
Enables/disables the option to collect btsnoop log from
chrome://bluetooth-internals

Name: kEnterprisePasswordReuseUiRefresh
Documentation: Enables showing an updated Password Reuse UI for enterprise users.

Name: kUseNewServiceWorkerTaskQueue
Documentation: If enabled, use the new simpler, more efficient service worker task queue.

Name: kCommittedOriginEnforcements
Documentation:
Turn on enforcements based on tracking the list of committed origins in
ChildProcessSecurityPolicy::CanAccessMaybeOpaqueOrigin(). Note that this only
controls whether or not the new security checks take effect; when this is
off, the security check is still performed and compared to the legacy jail
and citadel check to collect data about possible mismatches. Requires
CommittedOriginTracking to also be turned on to take effect. See
https://crbug.com/40148776.

Name: kEnableADPFGpuCompositorThread
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome includes the Compositor GPU Thread into the
ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) hint session, instead
of the GPU Main Thread.
see https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/e7507d15614ac7f499fb89086b3a09772fa8deb4

Name: kLaunchedHistoryEmbeddings
Documentation: Do not use. For test only.

Name: kFledgeEnableUnNoisedRealTimeReport
Documentation: Enable un-noised real time reporting for certain user settings.

Name: kWebPaymentsJustInTimePaymentApp
Documentation: Used to control whether allow crawling just-in-time installable payment app.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAdsAPIsM1Override
Documentation:
Enables exposure of the core milestone 1 (M1) APIs in the renderer without an
origin trial token: Attribution Reporting, FLEDGE, Topics.

Name: kScrimForBrowserWindowModal
Documentation:
When enabled, a scrim is shown behind window modal dialogs to cover the
entire browser window. This gives user a visual cue that the browser window
is not interactable.

Name: kIndexedDBCompressValuesWithSnappy
Documentation:
Use Snappy to compress values for IndexedDB before wiring them to the
browser.

Name: kRemoveSearchboxStatsParamFromPrefetchRequests
Documentation:
Kill switch to revert the fix of dropping searchbox stats (gs_lcrp) from
prefetch requests. See crbug.com/350939001.

Name: kNtpPhotosModuleCustomizedOptInTitle
Documentation: If enabled, a customized title will be shown on the opt-in card.

Name: kFledgeOriginScopedKeys
Documentation: See https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/issues/1334

Name: kEnableStaticCTAPIEnforcement
Documentation:
Kill switch for Static CT Log (aka Tiled Log aka Sunlight)
enforcements in Certificate Transparency policy checks. If disabled, SCTs
from Static CT Logs will simply be ignored.

Name: kWalrusUseProdServer
Documentation: Enables Walrus Prod Server

Name: kUseSnappyForParkableStrings
Documentation:
Enabling this will cause parkable strings to use Snappy for compression iff
kCompressParkableStrings is enabled.

Name: kSendBeaconThrowForBlobWithNonSimpleType
Documentation: Make sendBeacon throw for a Blob with a non simple type.

Name: kOmniboxAnswerActions
Documentation: Action Chips for Answer Suggestions.
