more details.

Name: kDocumentProvider
Documentation: Document provider and domain suggestions

Name: kEnableSearchAggregatorPolicy
Documentation: Enterprise search aggregators features.

Name: kTimerSlackMac
Documentation:
Under this feature, slack is added on mac message pumps that support it when
allowed per DelayPolicy.

Name: kClearUserDataUponProfileDestruction
Documentation: Killswitch that guards clearing all user data in the ProfileImpl destructor.

Name: kMessagesCloseButton
Documentation: Feature that enables a close button when mouses hovers over.

Name: kSuppressesSearchPrefetchOnSlowNetwork
Documentation: If enabled, suppresses SearchPrefetch (https://crbug.com/350519234)

Name: kShoppingAlternateServer
Documentation: Force traffic to alternate Chrome shopping server.

Name: kDocumentProviderEnterpriseEligibilityWhenUnknown
Documentation:
If enabled, the enterprise eligibility requirement for Drive suggestions
is considered met even when the account capability is unknown. Has no effect
if kDocumentProviderEnterpriseEligibility is disabled.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformIosModuleRanker
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling ios module ranker.

Name: kCapReferrerToOriginOnCrossOrigin
Documentation:
When kCapReferrerToOriginOnCrossOrigin is enabled, HTTP referrers on cross-
origin requests are restricted to contain at most the source origin.

Name: kBtmDualUse
Documentation: Enables Bounce Tracking Mitigations for Dual Use sites.

Name: kOmniboxAsyncViewInflation
Documentation: Enable asynchronous Omnibox/Suggest view inflation.

Name: kEnterpriseProfileBadgingForAvatar
Documentation:
Enables enterprise profile badging for managed profiles on the toolbar
avatar. On managed profiles, a "Work" or "School" label will be used in the
toolbar.

Name: kWebAudioRemoveAudioDestinationResampler
Documentation:
This feature flag controls whether the WebAudio destination resampler is
bypassed. When enabled, if the WebAudio context's sample rate differs from
the hardware's sample rate, the resampling step that normally occurs within
the WebAudio destination node is skipped. This allows the AudioService to
handle any necessary resampling, potentially reducing latency and overhead.

Name: kMostVisitedTilesNewScoring
Documentation: Most Visited Tiles scoring function changes.

Name: kDiscountAutofill
Documentation: Feature flag for showing discounts on checkout autofill.

Name: kDataSharingNonProductionEnvironment
Documentation:
Feature flag for server environment configuration based on string> By default
autopush server environment is set.

Name: kCompressReportingPipeline
Documentation:
Feature to enable/disable compression.
By default compression is disabled, until server can support compression.

Name: kAutofillEnablePaymentSettingsCardPromoAndScanCard
Documentation:
When enabled, the payment settings page will show a card promo and allow for
card scans.

Name: kSharedDictionaryRegisterNavigationRequests
Documentation:
When this feature, the kCompressionDictionaryTransport and
the kCompressionDictionaryTransportBackend features are enabled then the
response to a main-frame navigation request may be registered as a
dictionary if the response header contains a `use-as-dictionary` header.

Name: kReducedReferrerGranularity
Documentation: Parameters for kReduceUserAgentPlatformOsCpu;

Name: kCpssQuietChipTextUpdate
Documentation:
When enabled, Quiet prompts triggered by CPSS will have "Get Notifications?"
as the the chip text instead of the usual "Notifications Blocked".

Name: kExtensionManifestV2DeprecationWarning
Documentation:
Controls displaying a warning that affected MV2 extensions may no longer be
supported.

Name: kExtensionDisableUnsupportedDeveloper
Documentation: If enabled, disables unpacked extensions if developer mode is off.

Name: kMostVisitedTilesVisualDeduplication
Documentation: Most Visited Tiles Visual Deduplication.

Name: kSameSiteDefaultChecksMethodRigorously
Documentation:
When enabled, the SameSite by default feature does not add the
"Lax-allow-unsafe" behavior. Any cookies that do not specify a SameSite
attribute will be treated as Lax only, i.e. POST and other unsafe HTTP
methods will not be allowed at all for top-level cross-site navigations.
This only has an effect if the cookie defaults to SameSite=Lax.

Name: kEwalletPayments
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will offer to pay with eWallet accounts if a payment
link is detected.

Name: kOmniboxRestoreInvisibleFocusOnly
Documentation: Only restore focus when invisible.

Name: kOnDeviceClustering
Documentation: Enables configuring the on-device clustering backend.

Name: kV8SparkplugNeedsShortBuiltinCalls
Documentation:
Makes sure the experimental Sparkplug compiler is only enabled if short
builtin calls are enabled too.

Name: kOmitCorsClientCert
Documentation:
Do not send TLS client certificates in CORS preflight. Omit all client certs
and continue the handshake without sending one if requested.

Name: kLensOverlayCornerSliders
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay simplified selection flow.

Name: kGroupSuggestionService
Documentation: Enable the tab group suggestion service.

Name: kAutofillEnableLabelPrecedenceForTurkishAddresses
Documentation:
When enabled, the precedence is given to the field label over the name when
they match different types. Applied only for parsing of address forms in
Turkish.
TODO(crbug.com/40735892): Remove once launched.

Name: kOriginTrialStateHostApplyFeatureDiff
Documentation:
Kill-switch for any calls to the mojo interface OriginTrialStateHost
in the RuntimeFeatureStateOverrideContext class. If
`kOriginTrialStateHostApplyFeatureDiff` is disabled,
origin/deprecation trial token information is not sent to the browser
process.

Name: kSetLowPriorityForBeacon
Documentation:
When enabled, beacons (and friends) have ResourceLoadPriority::kLow,
not ResourceLoadPriority::kVeryLow.

Name: kKalmanDirectionCutOff
Documentation:
Enables discarding the prediction if the predicted direction is opposite from
the current direction.

Name: kThirdPartyStoragePartitioning
Documentation:
Enables partitioning of third party storage (IndexedDB, CacheStorage, etc.)
by the top level site to reduce fingerprinting.

Name: kHeavyAdPrivacyMitigations
Documentation:
Enables or disables the privacy mitigations for the heavy ad intervention.
This throttles the amount of interventions that can occur on a given host in
a time period. It also adds noise to the thresholds used. This is separate
from the intervention feature so it does not interfere with field trial
activation, as this blocklist is created for every user, and noise is decided
prior to seeing a heavy ad.

Name: kNativeNotifications
Documentation:
Enables the use of system notification centers instead of using the Message
Center for displaying the toasts. The feature is hardcoded to enabled for
Chrome OS.

Name: kAcceptCHFrame
Documentation:
Enable support for ACCEPT_CH H2/3 frame as part of Client Hint Reliability.
See:
https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-davidben-http-client-hint-reliability-02#section-4.3

Name: kUseLayerListsByDefault
Documentation:
When enabled, the LayerTreeHost will expect to use layer lists instead of
layer trees by default; the caller can explicitly opt into enabled or
disabled if need be to override this.

Name: kReduceSubresourceResponseStartedIPC
Documentation:
When enabled, sends SubresourceResponseStarted IPC only when the user has
allowed any HTTPS-related warning exceptions. From field data, ~100% of
subresource notifications are not required, since allowing certificate
exceptions by users is a rare event. Hence, if user has never allowed any
certificate or HTTP exceptions, notifications are not sent to the browser.
Once we start sending these messages, we keep sending them until all
exceptions are revoked and browser restart occurs.

Name: kShowRelatedWebsiteSetsPermissionGrants
Documentation:
When enabled, blocks condition to exclude auto granted permissions for
storage access exceptions. This will allow RWS permission grants to be
visible in the Embedded content settings page.

Name: kDocumentProviderEnterpriseEligibility
Documentation:
If enabled, the primary account must be subject to enterprise policies in
order to receive Drive suggestions.

Name: kAXRandomizedStressTests
Documentation:
Randomly turn the accessibility engine on based on certain conditions. We do
not put this flag in chrome://flags so we can get the cleanest data possible.

Name: kAdditionalOpaqueOriginEnforcements
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryption
Documentation:
Enables hardware secure decryption if supported by hardware and CDM.
NOTE: This feature is experimental and not officially supported. Users may
encounter issues; enabling is discouraged.
TODO(xhwang): Currently this is only used for development of new features.
Apply this to Android and ChromeOS as well where hardware secure decryption
is already available.

Name: kSmallerInterestArea
Documentation: Feature to reduce the area in which invisible tiles are kept around.

Name: kAutofillUseSubmittedFormInHtmlSubmission
Documentation:
Uses AutofillAgent::GetSubmittedForm() in HTML submissions.
See `AutofillAgent::GetSubmittedForm()` for more documentation.
TODO(crbug.com/40281981): Remove when launched.

Name: kNetworkServiceSandbox
Documentation:
Enables network service sandbox.
(Only causes an effect when feature kNetworkServiceInProcess is disabled.)

Name: kTabHoverCardImages
Documentation:
Enables preview images in tab-hover cards.
https://crbug.com/928954

Name: kSafetyCheckUnusedSitePermissions
Documentation: Feature to enable the unused site permissions module of Safety Check.

Name: kWebAuthnImmediateGet
Documentation: Enables the immediate mediation for `navigator.credentials.get` requests.

Name: kEnableWebHidInWebView
Documentation:
If enabled, <webview>s will be allowed to request permission from an
embedding Chrome App to request access to Human Interface Devices.

Name: kExtensionsMenuAccessControlWithPermittedSites
Documentation:
If enabled, user permitted sites are granted access. This should only happen
if kExtensionsMenuAccessControl is enabled, since it's the only entry point
where user could set permitted sites.

Name: kNtpOneGoogleBarAsyncBarParts
Documentation: If enabled, the OGB loader will request for the async bar parts payload type.

Name: kNotificationOneTapUnsubscribe
Documentation:
Adds an "Unsubscribe" action to web push notifications that allows stopping
notifications from a given origin with a single tap (with an option to undo).

Name: kVizNullHypothesis
Documentation:
Null Hypothesis test for viz. This will be used in an meta experiment to
judge finch variation.

Name: kCheckHTMLParserBudgetLessOften
Documentation:
If enabled, the HTMLDocumentParser will only check its budget after parsing a
commonly slow token or for one out of 10 fast tokens. Note that this feature
is a no-op if kTimedHTMLParserBudget is disabled.

Name: kOptimizationHints
Documentation:
Enables the syncing of the Optimization Hints component, which provides
hints for what optimizations can be applied on a page load.

Name: kWriteBookmarkWithoutTitle
Documentation: Copy bookmark and write url format to clipboard with empty title.

Name: kNtpFeedModule
Documentation: If enabled, Following Feed module will be shown.

Name: kEnablePixAccountLinking
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will prompt users without linked Pix accounts to link
their Pix accounts to Google Wallet.

Name: kApiEnterpriseKioskInput
Documentation: Controls the availability of the enterprise.kioskInput API.

Name: kMediaCodecCodedSizeGuessing
Documentation: Allow FrameInfoHelper to guess coded size information for MediaCodec frames.

Name: kFillRecoveryPassword
Documentation: Allows filling from a secondary recovery password saved as a backup.

Name: kFencedFramesAutomaticBeaconCredentials
Documentation:
Temporarily un-disable credentials on fenced frame automatic beacons until
third party cookie deprecation.
TODO(crbug.com/1496395): Remove this after 3PCD.

Name: kLiveCaptionLogFlickerRate
Documentation:
Log the amount of flickering between partial results. This measures how often
the system revises earlier outputs, to quantify the system's output
instability or flicker. Intuitively, it measures how many tokens must be
truncated from the previous text before appending any new text. The erasure
of the current timestep can be calculated from its longest common prefix with
the previous timestep.

Name: kPrefetchBrowserInitiatedTriggers
Documentation:
If enabled, browser-initiated prefetch is allowed.
Please see crbug.com/40946257 for more details.

Name: kDrawImmediatelyWhenInteractive
Documentation: If enabled, surface activation and draw do not block on dependencies.

Name: kNtpChromeCartModule
Documentation: If enabled, chrome cart module will be shown.

Name: kWebFeedOnboarding
Documentation: Feature that provides the user assistance in using the web feed.

Name: kTrackingProtection3pcd
Documentation: Feature to enable redesigned tracking protection UX + prefs for 3PCD.

Name: kUseInProgressDownloadManagerForDownloadService
Documentation:
Whether in-progress download manager will be used to initialize download
service.

Name: kAutofillOptimizeFormExtraction
Documentation:
When enabled, Autofill will try to reuse the result of previous form
extractions in subsequent functions that needs the form extracted, provided
we have guarantees that in the meantime the form couldn't have changed.

Name: kPrerender2EarlyDocumentLifecycleUpdate
Documentation:
Enables the prerendering page to perform prepaint document lifecycle updates
before activation. See https://crbug.com/336963892.
TODO( https://crbug.com/336963892): Make the expected DocumentLifecycle
status a feature parameter.

Name: kPushNotifications
Documentation: Enables push notification of hints.

Name: kOmniboxShortcutsAndroid
Documentation: `ShortcutsProvider` features.

Name: kMayLaunchUrlUsesSeparateStoragePartition
Documentation:
Enables an experimental feature which forces mayLaunchUrl to use a different
storage partition. This may reduce performance. This should not be enabled by
default.

Name: kNetworkAnnotationMonitoring
Documentation:
This feature enables monitoring of first-party network requests in order to
find possible violations. Example: A Chrome policy is set to disabled but the
network request controlled by that policy is observed.

Name: kStructuredMetrics
Documentation: This can be used to disable structured metrics as a whole.

Name: kFledgeUsePreconnectCache
Documentation:
Enables preconnecting to interest group owner origins and a bidding signals
URL origin at the start of an auction.

Name: kDisableArrayBufferSizeLimitsForTesting
Documentation:
TODO(https://crbug.com/1201109): temporary flag to disable new ArrayBuffer
size limits, so that tests can be written against code receiving these
buffers. Remove when the bindings code instituting these limits is removed.

Name: kAutofillEnableBuyNowPayLaterForKlarna
Documentation:
When enabled, buy now pay later (BNPL) for Klarna in Autofill will be
offered.

Name: kNetworkTimeServiceQuerying
Documentation: Feature that enables network time service querying.

Name: kServiceWorkerPaymentApps
Documentation:
Service worker based payment apps as defined by w3c here:
https://w3c.github.io/webpayments-payment-apps-api/
TODO(rouslan): Remove this.

Name: kUndoMigrationOfSyncingUserToSignedIn
Documentation:
If enabled, users who were migrated from syncing to signed-in via the above
flag are migrated back into the syncing state.

Name: kAutofillVcnEnrollRequestTimeout
Documentation: When enabled, adds a timeout on the network request for VcnEnroll requests.

Name: kPushSubscriptionWithExpirationTime
Documentation:
Feature flag to enable push subscription with expiration times specified in
/chrome/browser/push_messaging/push_messaging_constants.h

Name: kPartialLowEndModeOn3GbDevices
Documentation:
Force to enable LowEndDeviceMode partially on Android 3Gb devices.
(see PartialLowEndModeOnMidRangeDevices below)

Name: kExportFrameTimingAfterFrameDone
Documentation:
When enabled, moves the layer tree client's metric export call
for from beginning of the subsequent frame to the end of the subsequent
frame.

Name: kNtpPhotosModuleCustomizedOptInArtWork
Documentation: If enabled, a customized art work will be shown on the opt-in card.

Name: kDeclarativeNetRequestResponseHeaderMatching
Documentation:
Enables declarative net request rules to specify response headers as a
matching condition.

Name: kAutomaticFullscreenContentSetting
Documentation: LINT.ThenChange(//PRESUBMIT.py)

Name: kRuntimeOnMessagePromiseReturnSupport
Documentation:
Supports chrome.runtime.onMessage() returning a JS Promise to reply to sender
response callbacks. Promise resolve or rejection value will be sent to the
sender response callbacks.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformFedCmUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling FedCM user segment.

Name: kOriginKeyedProcessesByDefault
Documentation:
Enables origin-keyed processes by default, unless origins opt out using
Origin-Agent-Cluster: ?0. This feature only takes effect if the Blink feature
OriginAgentClusterDefaultEnable is enabled, since origin-keyed processes
require origin-agent-clusters.

Name: kAllBookmarksBaselineFolderVisibility
Documentation:
This feature controls the default visibility for permanent folders when
empty. It effectively swaps in "other bookmarks" as the default-visible
empty folder on mobile. This flag has no effect for desktop.

Name: kPreemptiveLinkToTextGeneration
Documentation: Enables link to text to be generated in advance.

Name: kNtpWallpaperSearchButton
Documentation:
If enabled, shows entry point on New Tab Page for Customize Chrome Side Panel
Wallpaper Search.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformCrossDeviceUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling cross device user segment.

Name: kMlUrlSearchBlending
Documentation:
If enabled, specifies how URL model scores integrate with search traditional
scores.

Name: kCookieDomainRejectNonASCII
Documentation: When enabled, cookies with a non-ASCII domain attribute will be rejected.

Name: kV8CodeMemoryWriteProtection
Documentation:
Enables W^X code memory protection in V8.
This is enabled in V8 by default. To test the performance impact, we are
going to disable this feature in a finch experiment.

Name: kThrottleMainFrameTo60Hz
Documentation:
On devices with a high refresh rate, whether to throttle main (not impl)
frame production to 60Hz.

Name: kXInput2KeyEvents
Documentation:
Chrome for Linux should eventually use XInput2 key events.
See https://crbug.com/412608405 for context.

Name: kResamplingInputEvents
Documentation: Enables resampling input events on main thread.

Name: kPopulatePermissionsPolicyOnRequest
Documentation:
If enabled, permissions policies relevant to a request are populated on
`network:ResourceRequest`.

Note: Policies are not guaranteed to be added on every path. If
`PermissionsPolicy` on the request is nullopt, you need to set it somewhere.

Name: kDeprecateUnload
Documentation:
Enables unload handler deprecation via Permissions-Policy.
https://crbug.com/1324111

Name: kOmniboxAction
Documentation:
Enables the Journeys Omnibox Action chip. `kJourneys` must also be enabled
for this to take effect.

Name: kNtpModulesLoad
Documentation:
If enabled, modules will be loaded but not shown. This is useful to determine
if a user would have seen modules in order to counterfactually log or
trigger.

Name: kPrivacySandboxMigratePrefsToSchemaV2
Documentation: If true, migrates Privacy Sandbox Notice & Consent prefs to V2.

Name: kV8SlowHistograms
Documentation:
Enables slow histograms that provide detailed information at increased
runtime overheads.

Name: kUseDnsHttpsSvcb
Documentation:
Enables querying HTTPS DNS records that will affect results from HostResolver
and may be used to affect connection behavior. Whether or not those results
are used (e.g. to connect via ECH) may be controlled by separate features.

Name: kTLSTrustAnchorIDs
Documentation:
Enables TLS Trust Anchor IDs
(https://tlswg.org/tls-trust-anchor-ids/draft-ietf-tls-trust-anchor-ids.html),
a TLS extension to help the server serve a certificate that the client will
trust.

Name: kTabGroupsSaveNudgeDelay
Documentation: Wrapper flag to control the nudge delay of the #tab-groups-save feature.

Name: kEnableComposeLanguageBypassForContextMenu
Documentation: Controls whether the language check is bypassed for the context menu option.

Name: kMdnsResponderGeneratedNameListing
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, the mDNS responder service responds to queries
for TXT records associated with
"Generated-Names._mdns_name_generator._udp.local" with a list of generated
mDNS names (random UUIDs) in the TXT record data.

Name: kOmitParametersInReadyToPay
Documentation:
If enabled, then the web merchant origin and web wallet parameters will be
omitted from the isReadyToPayRequest. See: https://crbug.com/1406655.

Name: kAdAuctionEventRegistration
Documentation:
Should Sec-Ad-Auction-Event-Recording-Eligible be sent on requests made
with attributionsrc, and should Ad-Auction-Register-Event responses on
those requests be processed?

Name: kV8EfficiencyModeTiering
Documentation: Use V8 efficiency mode for tiering decisions.

Name: kShowRecoveryPassword
Documentation:
Shows recovery password for the improved password change flow in the
management UI.

Name: kFieldClassificationModelCaching
Documentation:
When enabled, the field classification model uses runtime caching to not run
models on the same inputs multiple times.
TODO(crbug.com/371933424). Clean up when launched, if not used for Autofill
experiments.

Name: kSyncAutofillWalletCredentialData
Documentation: Controls whether to enable syncing of Autofill Wallet Credential Data.

Name: kFailedLoginDetectionBasedOnFormClearEvent
Documentation:
Marks form submission as failed whenever a password field is cleared for the
sign-in forms.

Name: kAutocompleteActionPredictorConfidenceCutoff
Documentation:
This is used to enable an experiment for modifying confidence cutoff of
prerender and preconnect for autocomplete action predictor.

Name: kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMediaAudio
Documentation:
If kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia is ENABLED, this flag controls
whether a "Share this tab instead" button should be enabled for
getDisplayMedia captures with audio.
If kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia is DISABLED, this flag has no
effect.
Note: This flag does not control if the "Share this tab instead" button is
shown for chrome.desktopCapture captures.

Name: kPrefetchReusable
Documentation:
If enabled, PrefetchContainer can be used for more than one navigation.
https://crbug.com/1449360

TODO(crbug.com/397882995): Remove this.

Name: kPrefetchQueueingPartialFixWithoutScheduler
Documentation:
Provide a partial fix for prefetch queueing problem (crbug.com/400233773),
without `PrefetchScheduler` feature.

Name: kPartitionAllocEventuallyZeroFreedMemory
Documentation:
Eventually zero out most PartitionAlloc memory. This is not meant as a
security guarantee, but to increase the compression ratio of PartitionAlloc's
fragmented super pages.

Name: kRestrictedWebUICodeCache
Documentation:
Restricts the WebUI scripts able to use the generated code cache according to
embedder-specified heuristics.

Name: kLegacyKeyRepeatSynthesis
Documentation:
Until recently, Chrome on most platforms relied solely on a heuristic in
ui::KeyEvent construction to determine if they are repeat key events. Chrome
recently shifted to reading key repeat information from the native OS key
event on all platforms (see https://crbug.com/40940886), which theoretically
makes this heuristic redundant.

This feature flag is used to gradually turn off this heuristic and also
serves as an emergency killswitch in case turning it off causes major
issues. See tracking bug https://crbug.com/411681432 for more info.

Name: kFocusTriggersWebAndSRPZeroSuggest
Documentation: Local history zero-prefix (aka zero-suggest) and prefix suggestions.

Name: kKAnonymityServiceOHTTPRequests
Documentation:
When enabled, the k-Anonymity Service will send requests to the Join and
Query k-anonymity servers.

Name: kSendExplicitDecodeRequestsImmediately
Documentation:
When enabled HTMLImageElement::decode() will initiate the decode task right
away rather than piggy-backing on the next BeginMainFrame.

Name: kV8ConcurrentSparkplug
Documentation: Enables the concurrent Sparkplug compiler.

Name: kDesktopScreenshots
Documentation:
Feature flag to enable the screenshots feature, currently accessed only
through the sharing hub.

Name: kIsolateFencedFrames
Documentation:
Enables process isolation of fenced content (content inside fenced frames)
from non-fenced content. See
https://github.com/WICG/fenced-frame/blob/master/explainer/process_isolation.md
for rationale and more details.

Name: kWebauthnDisabledOnAuto
Documentation:
Disables WebAuthn on Android Auto. Default enabled in M137, remove in or
after M140.

Name: kThreeAdsAPIsNoticeModalFeature
Documentation: ROW Notice Features

Name: kMessagesForAndroidFullyVisibleCallback
Documentation:
Feature that exposes a listener to notify whether the current message
is fully visible.

Name: kWebRtcEncryptedRtpHeaderExtensions
kEnforcePrivacySandboxAttestations
Documentation: Enables enforcement of Privacy Sandbox Enrollment/Attestations.

Name: kLensOverlay
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay.

Name: kMerchantTrustEvaluationControlSurvey
Documentation:
Enables the 'Merchant trust' sentiment survey for control group. Used for
feature evaluation. This should be set in the fieldtrial config along with
the trigger ID for the corresponding survey (as en_site_id) and probability
(as probability).

Name: kWebFontsCacheAwareTimeoutAdaption
Documentation:
Enables cache-aware WebFonts loading. See https://crbug.com/570205.
The feature is disabled on Android for WebView API issue discussed at
https://crbug.com/942440.

Name: kLCPTimingPredictorPrerender2
Documentation:
If enabled, Prerender2 by Speculation Rules API is delayed until
LCP is finished.

Name: kTouchDragAndDrop
Documentation: This feature enables drag and drop using touch input devices.

Name: kLCPPAutoPreconnectLcpOrigin
Documentation: If enabled, LCP image origin is predicted and preconnected automatically.

Name: kMediaControlsExpandGesture
Documentation:
Enable a gesture to make the media controls expanded into the display cutout.
TODO(beccahughes): Remove this.

Name: kPasswordManagerLogToTerminal
Documentation:
Enables logging the content of chrome://password-manager-internals to the
terminal.

Name: kUiCompositorScrollWithLayers
Documentation: Enables scrolling with layers under ui using the ui::Compositor.

Name: kEnterpriseBadgingForNtpFooter
Documentation:
Enables enterprise badging for managed bnpwser on the new tab page footer.
On managed browsers, a building icon and "Managed by <domain>" string will be
shown in the footer, unless the icon and label are customized by the admin.

Name: kDevToolsImprovedNetworkError
Documentation:
Improves the signal-to-noise ratio of network error related messages in the
DevTools Console.
See http://crbug.com/40788570.

Name: kDelayUnsafeAds
Documentation:
Enables the artificial delaying of ads that are considered unsafe (e.g. http
or same-domain to the top-level).

Name: kUseGles2ForOopR
Documentation: Used to limit GL version to 2.0 for skia raster and compositing.

Name: kLiveCaptionExperimentalLanguages
Documentation: Enable experimental Live Caption languages.

Name: kProcessPerSiteSkipDevtoolsUsers
Documentation:
The default behavior to opt devtools users out of
kProcessPerSiteUpToMainFrameThreshold.

Name: kKeepWhitespaceForDataUrls
Documentation: Keep whitespace for non-base64 encoded data: URLs.

Name: kWebPaymentsSingleAppUiSkip
Documentation:
Used to control whether the Payment Sheet can be skipped for Payment Requests
with a single URL based payment app and no other info requested.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformTabletProductivityUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling tablet productivity user segment.

Name: kPartitionAllocAdjustSizeWhenInForeground
Documentation:
When set, partitions use a larger ring buffer and free memory less
aggressively when in the foreground.

Name: kAutofillNewSuggestionGeneration
Documentation:
If enabled, the new suggestion generation logic is used.
TODO(crbug.com/409962888): Remove once launched.

Name: kTranslateRecentTarget
Documentation:
Enables or disables using the most recent target language as the default
target language option.

Name: kMediaDevicesSystemMonitorCache
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, media-device enumerations use a cache that is
invalidated upon notifications sent by base::SystemMonitor. If disabled, the
cache is considered invalid on every enumeration request.

Name: kProfileSignalsReportingEnabled
Documentation:
Enables the addition of device signals fields to Profile-level Chrome
Reports.

Name: kWebRtcAllowH265Receive
Documentation:
When enabled, allow H.265 codec to be used for receiving WebRTC streams.
Platform hardware H.265 decoder needs to be supported and enabled in order to
negotiate usage of H.265 in SDP in the direction of receiving.

Name: kIsHardwareBackedFixEnabled
Documentation:
Enables the fix for `UnexportableSigningKey::IsHardwareBacked` when
dealing with Windows software keys.
Enabled by default on M139. Remove in or after M142.

Name: kShowDomNodeIDs
Documentation: Enables showing DOM Node ID of elements.

Name: kAutofillSkipPreFilledFields
Documentation: If enabled, a pre-filled field will not be filled.

Name: kDeprecateUnloadByAllowList
Documentation:
Only used if `kDeprecateUnload` is enabled. The deprecation will only apply
if the host is on the allow-list.

Name: kProductSpecificationsClearMetadataOnNewlySupportedFields
Documentation:
Kill switch for unsupported fields becoming supported in the event of a
browser upgrade.

Name: kNtpOneGoogleBar
Documentation:
If enabled, OneGoogleBar will be shown.
This is a kill switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kSyntheticPointerActions
Documentation:
Dispatch touch events to "SyntheticGestureController" for events from
Devtool Protocol Input.dispatchTouchEvent to simulate touch events close to
real OS events.

Name: kNvidiaVpTrueHDR
Documentation: Allow overlay swapchain to use NVIDIA video processor for trueHDR.

Name: kMBIMode
Documentation:
The MBI mode controls whether or not communication over the
AgentSchedulingGroup is ordered with respect to the render-process-global
legacy IPC channel, as well as the granularity of AgentSchedulingGroup
creation. This will break ordering guarantees between different agent
scheduling groups (ordering withing a group is still preserved).
DO NOT USE! The feature is not yet fully implemented. See crbug.com/1111231.

Name: kPageTextExtraction
Documentation:
This feature flag does not turn off any behavior, it is only used for
experiment parameters.

Name: kFeedLoadingPlaceholder
Documentation:
Feature that shows placeholder cards instead of a loading spinner at first
load.

Name: kDiscardFrozenBrowsingInstancesWithGrowingPMF
Documentation:
When enabled, frozen browsing instances in which an origin's private memory
footprint grows above a threshold are discarded. Depends on
`kMemoryMeasurementInFreezingPolicy`.

Name: kAllowedMixedContentInlinePdf
Documentation: Whether mixed-content PDF links can be downloaded if opening inline.

Name: kPersonalizeFeedUnsignedUsers
Documentation: Personalize feed for unsigned users.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryConfiguration
Documentation:
Allows the Extension Telemetry Service to accept and use configurations
sent by the server.

Name: kNtpMiddleSlotPromo
Documentation:
If enabled, middle slot promo will be shown.
This is a kill switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kAllowNonFamilyLinkUrlFilterMode
Documentation:
Allows the URL classification mode without credentials, if the profile is not
managed by the family link System.

Name: kAndroidDragDropOopif
Documentation: Adds OOPIF support for android drag and drop.

Name: kAutofillModelPredictions
Documentation:
When enabled, all behaviours related to the on-device machine learning
model for field type predictions will be guarded.
TODO(crbug.com/40276177): Remove when launched.

Name: kRestrictDownloadOnSyncedTabs
Documentation:
Feature flag to restrict download on synced tabs if the navigation is
triggered without attention..

Name: kStylusSpecificTapSlop
Documentation:
Uses a stylus-specific tap slop region parameter for gestures.  Stylus taps
tend to slip more than touch taps (presumably because the user doesn't feel
the movement friction with a stylus).  As a result, it is harder to tap with
a stylus. This feature makes the slop region for stylus input bigger than the
touch slop.

Name: kMediaEngagementBypassAutoplayPolicies
Documentation:
The following Media Engagement flags are not enabled on mobile platforms:
- MediaEngagementBypassAutoplayPolicies: enables the Media Engagement Index
  data to be esude to override autoplay policies. An origin with a high MEI
  will be allowed to autoplay.
- PreloadMediaEngagementData: enables a list of origins to be considered as
  having a high MEI until there is enough local data to determine the user's
  preferred behaviour.

Name: kRunTasksByBatches
Documentation: Feature to run tasks by batches before pumping out messages.

Name: kScriptStreaming
Documentation: Controls script streaming for http and https scripts.

Name: kPlusAddressUserCreatedPlusAddressViaManualFallbackSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kAdsInterventionsEnforced
Documentation: Enables the blocking of ads on sites that have ads violations.

Name: kProfileSeparationDomainExceptionListRetroactive
Documentation:
Enables the fact that the ProfileSeparationDomainExceptionList retroactively
signs out accounts that require a new profile. This is used as a kill switch.

Name: kInterestGroupUpdateIfOlderThan
Documentation:
Enables the ability to use the updateIfOlderThanMs field in the trusted
bidding response to trigger a post-auction update if the group has been
updated more recently than updateIfOlderThanMs milliseconds, bypassing the
typical 24 hour wait.

Name: kStoreTitleInContentsAndUrlInDescription
Documentation:
Provider-specific - These features change the behavior of specific providers.
TODO(crbug.com/40179316): Clean up feature flag used in staged roll-out of
various CLs related to the contents/description clean-up work.

Name: kLocalWebApprovals
Documentation:
Enables local parent approvals for the blocked website on the Family Link
user's device.

Name: kBtmTtl
Documentation:
Flag used to control the TTL for user interactions (separately from the
|kBtm| feature flag).

Name: kBeforeUnloadBrowserResponseQueue
Documentation:
When enabled, the browser will schedule before unload tasks that continue
navigation network responses in a kHigh priority queue.
TODO(b/281094330): Run experiment on ChromeOS. Experiment was not run on
ChromeOS due to try bot issue.

Name: kEnableADPFSetThreads
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome uses SetThreads instead of recreating an
ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) hint session when the set of
threads in the session changes.

Name: kAccessibilityTreeForViews
Documentation: Expose the accessibility tree for views via an AXTree of AXNodes.

Name: kGooglePlayProtectReducesWarnings
Documentation: Whether Google Play Protect should supercede file-type warnings

Name: kAddWarningShownTSToClientSafeBrowsingReport
Documentation: Enables adding warning shown timestamp to client safe browsing report.

Name: kDefaultPassthroughCommandDecoder
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kUseAlternateHistorySyncIllustration
Documentation:
Feature flag to determine whether an alternate illustration should be used on
the history sync consent screen. This feature should be used independent of
any other features in this file.

Name: kDelayedWarnings
Documentation: Controls whether the delayed warning experiment is enabled.

Name: kIncludeJSCallStackInExtensionApiRequest
Documentation:
If enabled, include JS call stack data in the extension API request
sent to the browser process. This data is used for telemetry purpose
only.

Name: kContextualPageActions
Documentation:
Feature flag for enabling contextual page actions. Do not remove this, as all
segmentation platform powered functionalities must be behind a base::Feature.

Name: kUseRendererProcessPolicy
Documentation: Enables the renderer on Android to use a separate seccomp policy.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformUkmEngine
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling UKM based engine.

Name: kRelatedWebsiteSetsDevUI
Documentation:
Enables chrome://privacy-sandbox-internals/related-website-internals DevUI
page. Relies on PrivacySandboxInternalsDevUI also being enabled.

Name: kRenderBlockingFonts
Documentation:
Makes preloaded fonts render-blocking up to the limits below.
See https://crbug.com/1412861

Name: kAvoidEntryCreationForNoStore
Documentation: Avoid creating cache entries for transactions that are most likely no-store.

Name: kCastStreamingExponentialVideoBitrateAlgorithm
Documentation:
Controls whether the new exponential bitrate calculate logic is used, or
the legacy linear algorithm.

Name: kGroupNIKByJoiningOrigin
Documentation:
Group network isolation key(NIK) by storage interest group joining origin to
improve privacy and performance -- IGs of the same joining origin can reuse
sockets, so we don't need to renegotiate those connections.

Name: kWebHidAttributeAllowsBackForwardCache
Documentation:
When enabled, accessing the navigator.hid attribute does not prevent the
frame from entering the back forward cache.

Name: kRemoveCoreSiteInstance
Documentation:
Controls whether the core SiteInstance in ProcessManager is removed. This
also requires adjusting when some frames are registered with the
ProcessManager, since they are no longer created directly with an
extension's SiteInstance (and instead go through a host swap before commit).
TODO(https://crbug.com/334991035): Remove this feature after we're confident
nothing breaks.

Name: kAutofillImprovedLabels
Documentation:
When enabled, the autofill suggestion labels are more descriptive and
relevant.
TODO(crbug.com/380273791): Cleanup when launched.

Name: kUseParallelRequestsForHTTP2
Documentation: Whether parallel download is used for HTTP2 connections.

Name: kSyntheticCapabilities
Documentation:
When enabled, allows the server to unilaterally alter capabilities sent
by the client, primarily to retroactively work around bugs.

Name: kExtendedReportingRemovePrefDependency
Documentation:
Controls whether Safe Browsing Extended Reporting (SBER) is deprecated.
When this feature flag is enabled:
- the Extended Reporting toggle will not be displayed on
  chrome://settings/security
- features will not depend on the SBER preference value,
  safebrowsing.scout_reporting_enabled

Name: kHistoryEmbeddings
Documentation:
Please use `IsHistoryEmbeddingsFeatureEnabled()` instead of using any of
these features directly.
See chrome/browser/history_embeddings/history_embeddings_utils.h

Name: kBtm
Documentation:
Enables the BTM (Bounce Tracking Mitigation) feature.
On by default to allow for collecting metrics. All potentially dangerous
behavior (database persistence, storage deletion) will be gated by params.

Name: kEnforceFullDelegation
Documentation: Used to reject the apps with partial delegation.

Name: kResourceFetcherStoresStrongReferences
Documentation: Whether the ResourceFetcher should store strong references too.

Name: kTearOffWebAppTabOpensWebAppWindow
Documentation:
Enables creating a web app window when tearing off a tab with a url
controlled by a web app.

Name: kWebRtcHWDecoding
Documentation: Enables HW decode acceleration for WebRTC.

Name: kCheckIntentCallerPermission
Documentation:
When launching an intent, check whether the caller has the permission to
access a URI before returning the result.

Name: kTpcdTrialSettings
Documentation: Feature to enable consideration of 3PC deprecation trial settings.

Name: kCheckingNoExtensionIdInExtensionIpcs
Documentation:
When enabled, then bad_message::ReceivedBadMessage will be called when
browser receives an IPC from a content script and the IPC that unexpectedly
claims to act on behalf of a given extension id, (i.e. even if the browser
process things that renderer process never run content scripts from the
extension).

Name: kAllowSameSiteNoneCookiesInSandbox
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, servers can include an
allow-same-site-none-cookies value that notifies the browser that same-site
SameSite=None cookies should be allowed in sandboxed contexts with 3PC
restrictions.

Name: kForceOffTextAutosizing
Documentation:
Text autosizing uses heuristics to inflate text sizes on devices with
small screens. This feature is for disabling these heuristics.

Name: kAllowNonSecureOverlays
Documentation:
Should we allow video playback to use an overlay if it's not needed for
security?  Normally, we'd always want to allow this, except as part of the
power testing A/B experiment.  https://crbug.com/1081346 .

Name: kV8ExperimentalRegexpEngine
Documentation: Enables fallback to a breadth-first regexp engine on excessive backtracking.

Name: kEnableNewUploadSizeLimit
Documentation: Controls the new upload/download and print limit for content analysis.

Name: kAutofillRequireCvcForPossibleCardUpdate
Documentation:
When enabled, if credit card upload save encounters a card with the same four
digits as an existing server card but a different expiration date, it
requires that CVC was found in the flow before offering to save/update the
card.

Name: kCdmHostVerification
Documentation:
CDM host verification is enabled by default. Can be disabled for testing.
Has no effect if ENABLE_CDM_HOST_VERIFICATION buildflag is false.

Name: kZeroSuggestInMemoryCaching
Documentation:
If enabled, zero prefix suggestions will be stored using an in-memory caching
service, instead of using the existing prefs-based cache.

Name: kServiceWorkerSyntheticResponse
Documentation:
(crbug.com/352578800): Enables building a sysnthetic response by
ServiceWorker. For navigation requests, the pre-learned static response
header is returned in parallel with dispatching the network request.

Name: kIntelVpSuperResolution
Documentation: Allow overlay swapchain to use Intel video processor for super resolution.

Name: kVibration
Documentation: Enables vibration; an user gesture will still be required if enabled.

Name: kPrerender2AllowActivationInBackground
Documentation:
Allows activation in background tab. For now, this is used only on web
platform tests on macOS to run activation with target hint tests that have
race conditions between visibility change and activation start on a prerender
WebContents. Note that this issue does not happen on browser_tests, so this
could be specific to WPT setup.
TODO(crbug.com/40249964): Allow activation in background by default.

Name: kAlignSurfaceLayerImplToPixelGrid
Documentation:
When enabled, this forces composited textures for SurfaceLayerImpls to be
aligned to the pixel grid. Lack of alignment can lead to blur, noticeably so
in text. https://crbug.com/359279545

Name: kUseZstdForParkableStrings
Documentation: Use the zstd compression algorithm for ParkableString compression.

Name: kWebContentsDiscard
Documentation:
Enables a discard operation on WebContents to free associated resources.
Eliminates the need to destroy the WebContents object to free its resources.

Name: kQuicMigrationIgnoreDisconnectSignalDuringProbing
Documentation:
When enabled, network disconnect signals don't trigger immediate migration
when there is an ongoing migration with probing.

Name: kAutofillEnableLogFormEventsToAllParsedFormTypes
Documentation:
When enabled, a form event will log to all of the parsed forms of the same
type on a webpage. This means credit card form events will log to all credit
card form types and address form events will log to all address form types."
TODO(crbug.com/359934323): Clean up when launched

Name: kWebRtcPqcForDtls
Documentation:
This feature enables using Post-Quantum Crypto(PQC) for DTLS to improve
WebRTC's security.

Name: kPumpFastToSleepAndroid
Documentation:
Under this feature, the Android pump will call ALooper_PollOnce() rather than
unconditionally yielding to native to determine whether there exists native
work to be done before sleep.

Name: kContextMenuSearchForVideoFrame
Documentation: Enables the "Search Video Frame with <Search Provider>" context menu item.

Name: kClientSideDetectionForcedLlamaRedirectChainKillswitch
Documentation: Killswitch for Llama forced trigger info redirect chain check.

Name: kAutofillEnableImportWhenMultiplePhoneNumbers
Documentation:
Controls whether to save the first number in a form with multiple phone
numbers instead of aborting the import.
TODO(crbug.com/40742746) Remove once launched.

Name: kClearCrossSiteCrossBrowsingContextGroupWindowName
Documentation:
Clear the window.name property for the top-level cross-site navigations that
swap BrowsingContextGroups(BrowsingInstances).

Name: kNetworkContextPrefetchUseMatches
Documentation:
This feature makes the matching fetches performed by the Prefetch() actually
be consumed directly by renderers. When this is disabled, the disk cache
entry may be reused but the original URLLoader is cancelled. Does nothing
unless "NetworkContextPrefetch" is also enabled.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForParsingWithSharedLabels
Documentation:
Controls if the heuristic field parsing utilizes shared labels.
TODO(crbug.com/40741721): Remove once shared labels are launched.

Name: kFurtherOptimizeParsingDataUrls
Documentation: Further optimize parsing data: URLs.

Name: kSendTouchMovesToEventForwarderObservers
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/328601354): Cleanup flag after investigating nothing is broken
after changing the default behavior for EventForwarder observers.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformModelExecutionSampling
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling model execution report sampling.

Name: kSyncSupportAlwaysSyncingPriorityPreferences
Documentation:
If enabled, allowlisted priority preferences will be synced even if the
preferences user toggle is off. Note that this flag is only meaningful if
kEnablePreferencesAccountStorage is enabled.

Name: kSafetyHubDisruptiveNotificationRevocation
Documentation:
Automatically revoke disruptive notifications
in Safety Hub.

Name: kUseDMSAAForTiles
Documentation: Use DMSAA instead of MSAA for rastering tiles.

Name: kEnableTLS13EarlyData
Documentation: Enables TLS 1.3 early data.

Name: kNavigationPredictor
Documentation:
Used to control the collection of anchor element metrics (crbug.com/856683).
If kNavigationPredictor is enabled, then metrics of anchor elements
in the first viewport after the page load and the metrics of the clicked
anchor element will be extracted and recorded.
Note that the desktop roll out is being done separately from android. See
https://crbug.com/40258405

Name: kFledgePrepareBidderContextsInAdvance
Documentation:
Prepare bidder contexts, including running top level scripts, before
we're ready to generate a worklet's first bid.

Name: kAvoidCloneArgsOnExtensionFunctionDispatch
Documentation:
When enabled, a call to base::ListValue::Clone is avoided when dispatching an
extension function. Behind a feature to assess impact
(go/chrome-performance-work-should-be-finched).
TODO(crbug.com/424432184): Clean up when experiment is complete.

Name: kSharedWorkerBlobURLFix
Documentation:
If a blob URL is used for a SharedWorker script's URL, a controller will be
inherited.

Name: kEnterpriseSecurityEventReportingOnAndroid
Documentation: Controls whether event reporting is enabled on Android

Name: kLogTLSResumption
Documentation: Log TLS resumption.

Name: kAutofillEnableRankingFormulaAddressProfiles
Documentation:
When enabled, autofill will use the new ranking algorithm for address profile
autofill suggestions.

Name: kComposeUiParams
Documentation: Controls parameters around UI rendering.

Name: kPrivacySandboxActivityTypeStorage
Documentation: Enables Activity Type Storage

Name: kClayBlocking
Documentation:
Enables the blocking dialog that directs users to complete their choice of
default apps (for Browser & Search) in Android.

Name: kUseSharedRebindServiceConnection
Documentation:
Use shared service connection to rebind a service binding to update the LRU
in the ProcessList of OomAdjuster.

Name: kUnrestrictedSharedArrayBuffer
Documentation:
This feature is for a reverse Origin Trial, enabling SharedArrayBuffer for
sites as they migrate towards requiring cross-origin isolation for these
features.
TODO(bbudge): Remove when the deprecation is complete.
https://developer.chrome.com/origintrials/#/view_trial/303992974847508481
https://crbug.com/1144104

Name: kReportingServiceAlwaysFlush
Documentation:
Determines whether to always flush Local State immediately after an UMA/UKM
log upload. If this is disabled, Local State is only immediately flushed
after an upload if this is a mobile platform and the browser is in the
background.

Name: kWebTransportFineGrainedThrottling
Documentation: Enables a smarter throttling strategy based in the server's IP.

Name: kSyncEnablePasswordsSyncErrorMessageAlternative
Documentation:
Flag to test different alternatives for the passwords sync error message
content.

Name: kWebUITabStripContextMenuAfterTap
Documentation:
Controls whether the context menu is shown on a touch press or a touch
tap gesture on the WebUI Tab Strip.

Name: kClientHintsResourceWidth_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `width` client hint.

Name: kViewTransitionFloorTransform
Documentation:
When enabled, the view transition capture transform is floored instead of
rounded and we use the render surface pixel snapping to counteract the blurry
effect.

Name: kPlusAddressUserDidChoosePlusAddressOverEmailSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kAndroidAutofillLazyFrameworkWrapper
Documentation:
If enabled, the AutofillManagerWrapper class will not be initialized when the
AutofillProvider Java class is initialized. Some apps do not use Autofill at
all, yet they incur the latency cost of initializing the wrapper. This
experiment tests whether lazily initializing the wrapper will cause any
issues.

Name: kDisableMemoryReclaimerInBackground
Documentation: When enabled, disable the memory reclaimer in background.

Name: kFledgeSendDebugReportCooldownsToBandA
Documentation:
Send forDebuggingOnly's per ad tech cooldown statuses to B&A server side in
the request. Only lockout status is sent to B&A server side when this flag is
disabled.

Name: kVizFrameSubmissionForWebView
Documentation:
Submit CompositorFrame from SynchronousLayerTreeFrameSink directly to viz in
WebView.

Name: kFledgeModifyInterestGroupPolicyCheckOnOwner
Documentation:
Check if the owner of joinAdInterestGroup would be able to call
joinAdInterestGroup in its own subframe with allow=join-ad-interest-group.

Name: kAutofillSendUnidentifiedKeyAfterFill
Documentation:
If disabled (default for many years), autofilling triggers KeyDown and
KeyUp events that do not send any key codes. If enabled, these events
contain the "Unidentified" key.

Name: kWebAuthnRetryU2FErrors
Documentation: Retry requests to U2F keys after a delay if a low-level error happens.

Name: kHttpDiskCachePrewarming
Documentation: If enabled, prewarm HTTP disk cache based on the previous navigation.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformCollectTabRankData
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling data collection for tab ranking.

Name: kUnimportantFramesPriority
Documentation:
When enabled, visible unimportant frames receives a lesser priority than
non unimportant frames.

Name: kPrefetchPrivacyChanges
Documentation:
Prefetch request properties are updated to be privacy-preserving. See
crbug.com/988956.

Name: kMediaCapabilitiesQueryGpuFactories
Documentation:
When enabled, MediaCapabilities will check with GPU Video Accelerator
Factories to determine isPowerEfficient = true/false.

Name: kFrameTopHeader
Documentation:
When enabled, a `Sec-Fetch-Frame-Top` header will be emitted on
outgoing requests.

Name: kCheckWebAppExistenceAsync
Documentation:
Checking if a web app is installed in Chrome Android ultimately leads to a
long, UI-thread Binder call. Enabling this flag makes the web app
installation check on Clank async.

Name: kServiceWorkerStaticRouterRaceRequestFix
Documentation:
(crbug.com/340949948): Killswitch for the fix to address the ServiceWorker
main and subreosurce loader lifetime issue, which introduces fetch() failure
in the sw fetch handler.

Name: kDynamicSafeAreaInsetsSupportedByCC
Documentation:
The position affected by the safe area inset bottom will be handled by CC in
the Render Compositor Thread. The transform metrix y is adjusted for all
affected nodes.

Name: kIpProtectionUx
Documentation: Enables showing IP Protection toggle on the settings page.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformDeviceSwitcher
Documentation: Feature flag for device switcher segment.

Name: kCSPScriptSrcHashesInV1
Documentation:
When enabled, allowlisting script urls and scripts used in eval via hashes
will be supported in script-src.

Name: kAudioWorkletThreadPool
Documentation:
A thread pool system for effective usage of RealtimeAudioWorkletThread
instances.

Name: kDeferAudioFocusUntilAudible
Documentation:
Defer requesting persistent audio focus until the WebContents is audible.
The goal is to prevent silent playback from taking audio focus from
background apps on android, where focus is typically exclusive.

Name: kSafelistPaytoToRegisterProtocolHandler
Documentation:
When enabled, it adds Payto URI Scheme to the safe list for
registerProtocolHandler. This feature is disabled by default
Payto URI Scheme explanation https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8905
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/system-state.html#safelisted-scheme

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcWindowZeroHz
Documentation: This flag only has an effect if kWebRtcAllowWgcWindowCapturer is enabled.

Name: kVulkanFromANGLE
Documentation: Enable sharing Vulkan device queue with ANGLE's Vulkan backend.

Name: kPath2DPaintCache
Documentation:
Enables the use of the PaintCache for Path2D objects that are rasterized
out of process.  Has no effect when kCanvasOopRasterization is disabled.

Name: kSimdutfBase64Support
Documentation: Use the simdutf library to base64 decode data: URLs.

Name: kPrivacySandboxNoticeQueue
Documentation:
If true, adds the privacy sandbox notice to product messaging controller
queue.

Name: kSupportMultipleServerRequestsForPixPayments
Documentation: When enabled, Pix will be able to send multiple server request at a time.

Name: kAutofillEnableShowSaveCardSecurelyMessage
Documentation:
When enabled, save card securely message be displayed on upload card
UI message.

Name: kBackForwardCacheEmitZeroSamplesForKeyMetrics
Documentation:
Enables to emit zero values for some key metrics when back-forward cache is
used.

With this flag disabled, no samples are emitted for regular VOLT metrics
after the page is restored from the back-forward cache. This means that we
will miss a lot of metrics for history navigations after we launch back-
forward cache. As metrics for history navigations tend to be better figures
than other navigations (e.g., due to network cache), the average of such
metrics values will become worse and might seem regression if we don't take
any actions.

To mitigate this issue, we plan to emit 0 samples for such key metrics for
back-forward navigations. This is implemented behind this flag so far, and we
will enable this by default when we reach the conclusion how to adjust them.

For cumulative layout shift scores, we use actual score values for back-
forward cache navigations instead of 0s.

Name: kNtpPhotosModuleSoftOptOut
Documentation: If enabled, Google Photos opt-in card will show a button to soft opt-out.

Name: kMantaService
Documentation:
This flag is used for enabling the Manta Service, a profile keyed service for
the google chrome Manta project.

Name: kAutofillEnableEmailOrLoyaltyCardsFilling
Documentation:
When enabled, Autofill will display joined email and loyalty card Autofill
suggestions.
TODO(crbug.com/416664590): Remove once launched.

Name: kSitePerProcess
Documentation:
Alternative to switches::kSitePerProcess, for turning on full site isolation.
Launch bug: https://crbug.com/810843.  This is a //chrome-layer feature to
avoid turning on site-per-process by default for *all* //content embedders
(e.g. this approach lets ChromeCast avoid site-per-process mode).

TODO(alexmos): Move this and the other site isolation features below to
browser_features, as they are only used on the browser side.

Name: kFontSrcLocalMatching
Documentation:
Enables fixes for matching src: local() for web fonts correctly against full
font name or postscript name. Rolling out behind a flag, as enabling this
enables a font indexer on Android which we need to test in the field first.

Name: kTabStripBrowserApi
Documentation: Controls whether to use the TabStrip browser api's controller.

Name: kOnBeginFrameThrottleVideo
Documentation:
if enabled, Any CompositorFrameSink of type video that defines a preferred
framerate that is below the display framerate will throttle OnBeginFrame
callbacks to match the preferred framerate.

Name: kTracingServiceInProcess
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values
in the .cc file.

Name: kHideDelegatedFrameHostMac
Documentation:
On mac, when the RenderWidgetHostViewMac is hidden, also hide the
DelegatedFrameHost. Among other things, it unlocks the compositor frames,
which can saves hundreds of MiB of memory with bfcache entries.

Name: kSavePasswordsContextualUi
Documentation:
Determines whether the "save password" page action displays different UI if
the user has said to never save passwords for that site.

Name: kBoostImageSetLoadingTaskPriority
Documentation: Boost the priority of certain loading tasks (https://crbug.com/1470003).

Name: kRequireLeadingInTextViewWithLeading
Documentation:
Kill switch to turn off validation in TextViewWithLeading that requires a
leading value to be configured.

Name: kOriginTrialsSampleAPIThirdPartyAlternativeUsage
Documentation:
Sample field trial feature for testing alternative usage restriction in
origin trial third party tokens.
 - While not used in production code, the feature must be kept for tests in
   components/embedder_support/origin_trials/origin_trial_policy_impl_unittest.cc.

Name: kPageHideEventForPrerender2
Documentation:
Firing pagehide events for intended prerender cancellation. See
crbug.com/353628449 for more details.

Name: kIPHDummyGroup
Documentation: A feature to ensure all arrays can contain at least one group.

Name: kTabGroupSyncServiceDesktopMigration
Documentation:
Feature flag specific to Desktop platforms. When enabled, desktop platforms
will use the TabGroupSyncService. When disabled, desktop platforms will
continue to use SavedTabGroupKeyedService.

Name: kPreloadSystemFonts
Documentation: If enabled, some system fonts are preloaded.

Name: kSubframeProcessReuseThresholds
Documentation:
Controls whether subframe process reuse should be restricted according to
resource usage policies. Namely, a process that is already consuming too
much memory is not attempted to be reused.

Name: kContextMenuSaveVideoFrameAs
Documentation: Enables the "Save Video Frame As" context menu item.

Name: kAutofillAddressUserDeclinedSuggestionSurvey
Documentation:
Feature flag controlling the display of surveys when a user does not
accept an Autofill suggestion. The goal is to understand the reason and work
towards improving acceptance.

Name: kZeroSuggestPrefetchingOnSRP
Documentation: Enables prefetching of the zero prefix suggestions for eligible users on SRP.

Name: kInputOnViz
Documentation:
If enabled, touch input on Android is handled on Viz process. The feature is
still in development and might not have any functional effects yet.
Design doc for InputVizard project for moving touch input to viz on Android:
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1mcydbkgFCO_TT9NuFE962L8PLJWT2XOfXUAPO88VuKE

Name: kPriceTrackingPromo
Documentation: Promotion in Magic Stack for Price Tracking users from other platforms.

Name: kPreloadingHeuristicsMLModel
Documentation:
If enabled, the machine learning model will be employed to predict the next
click for speculation-rule based pre-loadings.

Name: kV8OptimizeJavascript
Documentation: Enables optimization of JavaScript in V8.

Name: kWebAppManifestLockScreen
Documentation:
Controls parsing of the "lock_screen" dictionary field and its "start_url"
entry in web app manifests.  See explainer for more information:
https://github.com/WICG/lock-screen/
Note: the lock screen API and OS integration is separately controlled by
the content feature `kWebLockScreenApi`.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmationFallback
Documentation: Used to enable the refreshed fallback flow for Secure Payment Confirmation.

Name: kPartitionAllocUseSmallSingleSlotSpans
Documentation:
When enabled, uses a more nuanced heuristic to determine if slot
spans can be treated as "single-slot."

See also: https://crbug.com/333443437

Name: kCacheStorageCodeCacheHintHeader
Documentation:
When enabled allows the header name used in the blink
CacheStorageCodeCacheHint runtime feature to be modified.  This runtime
feature disables generating full code cache for responses stored in
cache_storage during a service worker install event.  The runtime feature
must be enabled via the blink runtime feature mechanism, however.

Name: kUseTaskRunnerForMojoAudioDecoderService
Documentation:
Feature flag to run the MojoAudioDecoderService in a sequence different than
the other mojo media services. On some Android devices, MediaCodec may block
the thread which leads to frequent audio decoder underrun in renderer.
Running the audio decoder in a separate sequence can improve the performance.
Note: running audio decoder in a separate thread/sequence will cause
multithread access to mojo media services. For Android audio decoder, the
thread safety is easier to guarantee because:
  1. The audio decoder and most of the other mojo media services don't cross
  reference each other.
  2. The only exception is CDM so we use a lock inside MojoCdmServiceContext
  for thread safety.

Name: kOnDeviceWebSpeech
Documentation: Enables the On-Device Web Speech feature on supported devices.

Name: kAccessibilityPageZoomV2
Documentation:
Enables the second iteration of AccessibilityPageZoom, which continues
the work completed in the first experiment and the subsequent fast-follow.
This version of the experiment explores enabling OS-level adjustments.

Name: kBlockAcceptClientHints
Documentation:
Enables the Accept-CH support disabler. If this feature is activated, Chrome
ignore Accept-CH response headers for a site that is specified in the
following kBlockAcceptClientHintsBlockedSite. This is used to compare Chrome
performance with a dedicated site.

Name: kKalmanHeuristics
Documentation: Enables changing the influence of acceleration based on change of direction.

Name: kPageInfoAboutThisSite
Documentation:
Controls the feature for English and other languages that are enabled by
default. Use IsAboutThisSiteFeatureEnabled() to check a specific language.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsPictureInPicture
Documentation: Show picture-in-picture button in Global Media Controls.

Name: kUseUtilityThreadGroup
Documentation:
Under this feature, a utility_thread_group will be created for
running USER_VISIBLE tasks.

Name: kV8NoReclaimUnmodifiedWrappers
Documentation: Disables reclaiming of unmodified wrappers objects.

Name: kLowLatencyCanvas2dImageChromium
Documentation:
Allow low latency canvas 2D to be in overlay (generally meaning scanned out
directly to display), even if regular canvas are not in overlay
(Canvas2DImageChromium is disabled).

Name: kSafeBrowsingCrxAllowlistShowWarnings
Documentation:
Controls whether we show an install friction dialog when an Enhanced Safe
Browsing user tries to install an extension that is not included in the
Safe Browsing CRX allowlist. This feature also controls if we show a warning
in 'chrome://extensions' for extensions not included in the allowlist.

Name: kAttributionReportingInBrowserMigration
Documentation:
Enables attribution reporting to be proxied via the browser process using the
same path as other fetch keepalive requests.
See https://crbug.com/1374121.

Name: kOmniboxMobileParityUpdate
Documentation:
Updates various NTP/Omnibox assets and descriptions for visual alignment on
Android and iOS.

Name: kVisualFeaturesSizes
Documentation:
Controls the behavior of visual features in CSD pings. This feature is
checked for the final size of the visual features and the minimum size of
the screen.

Name: kDataSharingFeature
Documentation:
Core feature flag for data sharing. Disabling this feature ensures an empty
implementation of the service is returned.

Name: kPostGetMyMemoryStateToBackground
Documentation: If enabled, getMyMemoryState IPC will be posted to background.

Name: kWebRtcApmDownmixCaptureAudioMethod
Documentation:
When enabled, overrides the Audio Processing Module parameter that controls
how multi-channel capture audio is downmixed to mono (when downmixing is
needed).

Name: kIsolateSandboxedIframes
Documentation:
Allow process isolation of iframes with the 'sandbox' attribute set. Whether
or not such an iframe will be isolated may depend on options specified with
the attribute. Note: At present, only iframes with origin-restricted
sandboxes are isolated.

Name: kSingleVideoFrameRateThrottling
Documentation:
If enabled, FrameRateDecider will toggle to half framerate if there's only
one video on screen whose framerate is lower than the display vsync and in
perfect cadence.

Name: kLocalListsUseSBv5
Documentation:
If enabled, fetching lists from Safe Browsing and performing checks on those
lists uses the v5 APIs instead of the v4 Update API. There is no change to
how often the checks are triggered (they are still not in real time).

Name: kEnableFingerprintingProtectionFilterInIncognito
Documentation: Toggle to enable/disable the Fingerprinting Protection Filter in Incognito.

Name: kRenderSurfacePixelAlignment
Documentation:
When enabled, for a render surface with fractional translation, we'll try to
align the texels in the render surface to screen pixels to avoid blurriness
during compositing.

Name: kMemoryCacheStrongReference
Documentation:
Keep strong references in the blink memory cache to maximize resource reuse.
See https://crbug.com/1409349.

Name: kPreloadTopChromeWebUI
Documentation:
Preloads a WebContents with a Top Chrome WebUI on BrowserView initialization,
so that it can be shown instantly at a later time when necessary.

Name: kServiceWorkerSrcdocSupport
Documentation:
(crbug.com/41411856): When enabled, the srcdoc iframes are controlled by the
same service worker that controls their parent.

Name: kV8ShortBuiltinCalls
Documentation: Enables short builtin calls feature.

Name: kAllowRTCEncodedVideoFrameSetMetadataAllFields
Documentation: Allow all fields to be set when calling RTCEncodedVideoFrame.setMetadata.

Name: kVisitedURLRankingSegmentationMetricsData
Documentation: Feature flag to disable the segmentation metrics transformer.

Name: kV8SlowHistogramsCodeMemoryWriteProtection
Documentation:
Multiple finch experiments might use slow-histograms. We introduce
separate feature flags to circumvent finch limitations.

Name: kAppStoreBilling
Documentation:
Used to control whether the invoking TWA can handle payments for app store
payment method identifiers.

Name: kNavigationPredictorNewViewportFeatures
Documentation:
Used to control the collection of new viewport related anchor element
metrics. Metrics will not be recorded if either this or kNavigationPredictor
is disabled.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsAutoDismiss
Documentation: Auto-dismiss global media controls.

Name: kNetworkServiceInProcess
Documentation: If the network service is enabled, runs it in process.

Name: kCustomizeChromeSidePanelExtensionsCard
Documentation:
If enabled, shows an extension card within the Customize Chrome Side
Panel for access to the Chrome Web Store extensions.

Name: kLensOverlayRoutingInfo
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay routing info optimizations.

Name: kAutofillEnableCardInfoRuntimeRetrieval
Documentation:
When enabled, runtime retrieval of CVC along with card number and expiry
from issuer for enrolled cards will be enabled during form fill.

Name: kRestartNetworkServiceUnsandboxedForFailedLaunch
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, the network service will restart unsandboxed if
a previous attempt to launch it sandboxed failed.

Name: kLoadingPredictorUseLocalPredictions
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kEnableServiceWorkersForChromeUntrusted
Documentation: Enables service workers on chrome-untrusted:// urls.

Name: kDropInputEventsWhilePaintHolding
Documentation:
Drop input events at the browser process until the process receives the first
signal that the renderer has sent a frame to cc (https://crbug.com/40057499).

Name: kPrivacyGuideAiSettings
Documentation: Enable AI settings page integration with Privacy Guide.

Name: kPrerender2NoVarySearch
Documentation:
This feature was used to launch Prerender2 support for No-Vary-Search header.
This work has finished and the old implementation was deleted. Now this flag
is just for injecting parameters through field trials as an umberella
feature.

Name: kSchedQoSOnResourcedForChrome
Documentation: Update scheduler settings using resourced on ChromeOS.

Name: kAutofillEnableLoyaltyCardsFilling
Documentation:
When enabled, Autofill will help users fill in loyalty card details.
TODO(crbug.com/395831853): Remove once launched.

Name: kGlicActor
Documentation: Controls whether the actor component of Glic is enabled.

Name: kConditionalImageResize
Documentation:
Set a RESIZE_BEST preference for image resizing algorithm in Client Side
Detection renderer processes for both image classification and image
embedding. This experiment is done to see if the resizing algorithm
preference will send clearer screenshots for server side evaluation.

Name: kCertificateTransparency
Documentation: Enables Certificate Transparency

Name: kAllowSubframeLocalWebApprovals
Documentation:
Whether supervised user can request local web approval from a blocked
subframe.

Name: kWebUsbBlocklist
Documentation:
This feature allows to dynamically introduce an additional list of devices
blocked by WebUSB via a Finch parameter. This parameter should be specified
in the Finch configuration to manage the list of blocked devices.

Name: kNewContentForCheckerboardedScrolls
Documentation:
When enabled, the CC tree priority will be switched to
NEW_CONTENT_TAKES_PRIORITY during long scroll that cause checkerboarding.

Name: kPageInfoAboutThisSiteMoreLangs
Documentation: Controls the feature for languages that are not enabled by default yet.

Name: kCompositorLoadingAnimations
Documentation:
Controls whether browser tab loading animations are driven by the compositor
vs. a repeating timer.

Name: kHttpsFirstModeV2ForTypicallySecureUsers
Documentation:
Enables HTTPS-First Mode for typically secure users. No-op if
HttpsFirstModeV2 or HTTPS-Upgrades is disabled.

Name: kUiCompositorUsesLayerLists
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/389771428): Switch the ui::Compositor to use
cc::PropertyTrees and layer lists rather than layer trees.

Name: kCompressBitmapAtBackgroundPriority
Documentation:
Used at callsites, to lower thread priority to background while compression
is happening.

Name: kDsePreload2OnSuggestNonDefalutMatch
Documentation:
Enables on-suggest prefetch for non default match.

For more details, see
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1f4dcNYP3O_Ft4yMmC42ETxGC5lM7YF5FDbEgnxUua7M/edit?tab=t.38v8gca76tmi

Name: kPolicyBlocklistProceedUntilResponse
Documentation:
Enable the PolicyBlocklistThrottle optimization to hide the DEFER latency
on WillStartRequest and WillRedirectRequest. See https://crbug.com/349964973.
This is launched, but the feature flag will be kept in 2025 for monitoring.

Name: kViewsAccessibilitySerializeOnDataChange
Documentation: Serialize Views' accessibility data as soon as it changes.

Name: kInputScenarioPriorityBoost
Documentation:
Boosts the priority of the renderer main thread if an input scenario is
detected.

Name: kSpecCompliantCanPlayThrough
Documentation: CanPlayThrough issued according to standard.

Name: kMultiBufferNeverDefer
Documentation:
Forces SuggestProviderState() to only suggest deferring when range requests
aren't supported and the underlying provider considers itself stale. The
stale state is set if the provider has been in a deferred state for > 1 sec.

Name: kAutofillAiNoTagTypes
Documentation:
If enabled, `*_TAG` types are replaced with dynamic attribute assignments.
This is a kill switch.

For example, if the feature is disabled, a passport name field requires a
`PASSPORT_NAME_TAG` prediction along with a classical `NAME_*` type.

If the feature is enabled, `PASSPORT_NAME_TAG` is ignored and the assignment
to the passport entity is derived from the surrounding fields.

TODO(crbug.com/422563282): Remove after the M140 branch point (2025-08-04).

Name: kMojoRecordUnreadMessageCount
Documentation:
Enables measurement of MessageChannel unread message counts. When enabled, a
small random selection of Connectors enable the unread message count quota
on their associated message pipe, and record the highest unread message count
seen during the Connector's lifetime.

Name: kEnableNtpBrowserPromos
Documentation: Advertises browser features in New Tab Page promos.

Name: kBakedGamutMapping
Documentation:
Redefine the oklab and oklch spaces to have gamut mapping baked into them.
https://crbug.com/1508329

Name: kForceFieldTrialSetupCrashForTesting
Documentation:
A testing feature that forces a crash during field trial creation
on developer and test builds.

Name: kAutofillEnableCardBenefitsForBmo
Documentation:
When enabled, card benefits offered by BMO will be shown in Payments Autofill
UI.

Name: kSuppressDifferentOriginSubframeJSDialogs
Documentation:
Disallows window.{alert, prompt, confirm} if triggered inside a subframe that
is not same origin with the main frame.

Name: kBatteryStatusManagerBroadcastReceiverInBackground
Documentation:
Enables registering & unregistering of the Battery Status Manager broadcast
receiver to the background thread.

Name: kDigitalGoodsApi
Documentation:
Controls whether the Digital Goods API is enabled.
https://github.com/WICG/digital-goods/

Name: kRequireHdcpKeyProvisioning
Documentation:
A temporary flag to require Content Protection to use provisioned key as the
kernel doesn't expose that it requires this yet.(b/112172923)

Name: kAutofillAiServerModel
Documentation:
If enabled, the client may trigger the server model for AutofillAI type
predictions.

Name: kIwaKeyDistributionDevMode
Documentation: Enables the key distribution dev mode UI on chrome://web-app-internals.

Name: kV8PerContextMarkingWorklist
Documentation: Enables per-context marking worklists in V8 GC.

Name: kQuicRegisterConnectionClosePayload
Documentation:
When enabled, QuicChromiumClientSession registers and unregisters QUIC
connection close payloads with the Android system service.

Name: kAutofillAcrossIframesIosTriggerFormExtraction
Documentation:
Controls whether to trigger form extraction when detecting a form activity on
a xframe form. Only effective when Autofill is enabled across iframes
(kAutofillAcrossIframesIos).

Name: kPauseBackgroundMutedAudio
Documentation: Pauses muted (and uncaptured) playbacks in the background.

Name: kEnforceNonceChecking
Documentation:
Enforce nonce checking when enabled.
If disabled, the nonce value returned from the device is not checked against
the one sent to the device. As a result, the nonce can be empty and omitted
from the signature. This allows backwards compatibility with legacy Cast
receivers.

Name: kBatterySaverModeAlignWakeUps
Documentation: If enabled, makes battery saver request heavy align wake ups.

Name: kComputePressureRateObfuscationMitigation
Documentation:
Enables rate obfuscation mitigation in compute pressure, to prevent
cross-channel attacks.

Name: kFedCmUpdatedCooldownPeriod
Documentation:
When enabled, FederatedIdentityApiEmbargoDurationDismiss will use values from
a field trial.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformComposePromotion
Documentation: Feature flag for Compose promotion targeting.

Name: kSensitiveContent
Documentation:
When enabled, the content view will be redacted if sensitive fields (such as
passwords or credit cards) are present on the page. The feature works only on
Android API level >= 35.
TODO(crbug.com/343119998): Clean up when launched.
